1
00:00:07,266 --> 00:00:09,902
[Stop Two: Namwon]

2
00:00:09,902 --> 00:00:11,471
- Huh?
- Yeah?

3
00:00:11,471 --> 00:00:13,105
[Welcoming the trio to Namwon]

4
00:00:13,105 --> 00:00:17,226
[Namwon pungmul troupe with soulful rhythms]

5
00:00:17,226 --> 00:00:20,213
[Joining in on the fun]

6
00:00:20,213 --> 00:00:22,715
Whoa, this is wild.

7
00:00:22,715 --> 00:00:25,401
[They hopped on a swing,
feeling like kids again]

8
00:00:25,401 --> 00:00:27,820
[Take a face-plant]

9
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:30,122
[That happened too, but...]

10
00:00:30,122 --> 00:00:31,192
Hello.

11
00:00:31,192 --> 00:00:32,593
- Hi there.
- I'm Park Seo Jun.

12
00:00:32,593 --> 00:00:33,633
You're Park Seo Jun?

13
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,828
[Meeting baby Park Seo Jun in Namwon]
Come here for a sec, come on over.

14
00:00:35,828 --> 00:00:38,493
[Seo Jun met Little Seo Jun too]

15
00:00:38,493 --> 00:00:39,992
[Phone-a-friend time from the day before]
- It's ringing! - Hey.

16
00:00:39,992 --> 00:00:41,313
Let me ask you something real quick.

17
00:00:41,313 --> 00:00:42,993
Can we use your place in Namwon?

18
00:00:42,993 --> 00:00:44,003
<i>Yeah, you can use it.</i>

19
00:00:44,003 --> 00:00:45,204
- Send me the address.
- Yeah.

20
00:00:45,204 --> 00:00:46,506
[Namwon stay secured through a friend!]

21
00:00:46,506 --> 00:00:49,261
[The trio rented a car to head to the stay]
[Parking lot]

22
00:00:49,261 --> 00:00:50,784
Unlocking.

23
00:00:50,784 --> 00:00:51,793
[Door unlocked successfully]
Yes.

24
00:00:51,793 --> 00:00:53,126
- Drop your bag.
- Got it.

25
00:00:53,126 --> 00:00:55,013
- Bag first.
- Bag.

26
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,110
Freedom.

27
00:00:56,110 --> 00:00:57,583
[Heavy bags loaded first]

28
00:00:57,583 --> 00:01:01,206
[Off they go, light as a feather]

29
00:01:01,206 --> 00:01:04,056
- This is so much easier with a car.
- It's the best.

30
00:01:04,056 --> 00:01:07,126
[Grocery run before the stay,
three minutes by car]

31
00:01:07,126 --> 00:01:09,656
[Random excitement on the way to the market]

32
00:01:09,656 --> 00:01:11,992
- It's right here.
- Yeah.

33
00:01:11,992 --> 00:01:14,333
Right turn into the lot.

34
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,460
[The car got them to the market in no time]

35
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:17,570
Yes.

36
00:01:17,570 --> 00:01:20,273
[Parking knocked out smoothly]

37
00:01:20,273 --> 00:01:22,408
[Door locked]

38
00:01:22,408 --> 00:01:24,277
Alright.

39
00:01:24,277 --> 00:01:26,193
[Grabbing a cart with excitement]

40
00:01:26,193 --> 00:01:27,660
This one should be enough for us, right?

41
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:29,982
Right? Let's grab the small one.

42
00:01:29,982 --> 00:01:32,669
[Heading in, hearts racing!]

43
00:01:32,669 --> 00:01:35,488
- Meat first?
- Yeah, meat first.

44
00:01:35,488 --> 00:01:38,391
[Past the eye-popping aisles...]

45
00:01:38,391 --> 00:01:40,791
[Arriving at the butcher section!]

46
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:43,026
- Whoa.
- Stew cut.

47
00:01:43,026 --> 00:01:45,983
- 12,000 won.
- Hey, that's a steal.

48
00:01:45,983 --> 00:01:47,266
Korean pork.

49
00:01:47,266 --> 00:01:48,834
[Hype maxed out at the sight of the price]

50
00:01:48,834 --> 00:01:51,003
Should we get pork belly and pork shoulder?

51
00:01:51,003 --> 00:01:52,095
Shoulder and belly?

52
00:01:52,095 --> 00:01:54,092
Yeah.

53
00:01:54,092 --> 00:01:55,695
- One more pack of belly?
- One more.

54
00:01:55,695 --> 00:01:58,674
- Or grab another pack of shoulder.
- What about you?

55
00:01:58,674 --> 00:01:59,879
35,000 won.

56
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:01,614
- All together?
- Yeah.

57
00:02:01,614 --> 00:02:03,355
Then should we grab some lettuce?

58
00:02:03,355 --> 00:02:04,474
Sure.

59
00:02:04,474 --> 00:02:05,827
- Man, it's cheap.
- Hold on.

60
00:02:05,827 --> 00:02:07,254
[Cheap prices, generous hearts]
So cheap.

61
00:02:07,254 --> 00:02:10,526
[Strolling around...]
Should we grab some ssamjang?

62
00:02:10,526 --> 00:02:12,391
Oh...

63
00:02:12,391 --> 00:02:13,992
- What about frozen belly?
- Overkill.

64
00:02:13,992 --> 00:02:15,972
- This plus frozen belly?
- Yeah.

65
00:02:15,972 --> 00:02:18,152
- Swap one belly for frozen.
- Sounds good.

66
00:02:18,152 --> 00:02:20,331
Since we've got the electric grill, right?

67
00:02:20,331 --> 00:02:22,101
- Frozen belly's good.
- It's the move.

68
00:02:22,101 --> 00:02:23,427
[Woo Shik's tip: thin slices cook fast]

69
00:02:23,427 --> 00:02:26,231
[Plan shift: One belly, one shoulder, frozen]
Yeah, frozen it is.

70
00:02:26,231 --> 00:02:28,473
[Cherry on top]
There's a ton in this one.

71
00:02:29,442 --> 00:02:31,577
[Looks plenty hefty]

72
00:02:31,577 --> 00:02:33,592
17,000 won, sounds good?

73
00:02:33,592 --> 00:02:35,011
- How about this?
- Looks good.

74
00:02:35,011 --> 00:02:38,150
Ssam sauce... oh, nice!

75
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,485
[Treasurer Park approves frozen and ssamjang]

76
00:02:39,485 --> 00:02:41,467
- We're getting this.
- Yeah.

77
00:02:41,467 --> 00:02:42,908
I'll go grab the lettuce.

78
00:02:42,908 --> 00:02:45,247
- Cool, I'll grab the ramyeon.
- Yeah.

79
00:02:45,247 --> 00:02:48,093
[Mains locked, divide and conquer]
You go pick whatever you want.

80
00:02:48,887 --> 00:02:52,693
Samyang, spicy savory flavor.

81
00:02:52,693 --> 00:02:54,468
Snack Ramyeon's pretty good too.

82
00:02:54,468 --> 00:02:55,568
Snack Ramyeon.

83
00:02:55,568 --> 00:02:57,536
3,480 won.

84
00:02:57,536 --> 00:02:59,728
- It's tasty.
- You're checking prices on ramyeon too?

85
00:02:59,728 --> 00:03:01,347
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

86
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:03,187
Samyang Ramyeon does taste good, though.

87
00:03:03,187 --> 00:03:05,011
3,600 won.

88
00:03:05,011 --> 00:03:06,779
[Two go silent over a 200 won gap...]

89
00:03:06,779 --> 00:03:08,284
[Tsk...]

90
00:03:08,284 --> 00:03:09,860
Want to do Samyang? Let's go Samyang.

91
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:11,656
[About to roll with Woo Shik's pick]
Samyang, then?

92
00:03:11,656 --> 00:03:13,319
- Is this a new one?
- Hold up, this one's three...

93
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:15,860
Ansungtangmyeon is 3,200 won.

94
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:18,217
- Ansungtangmyeon's tasty too.
- Let's grab it.

95
00:03:18,217 --> 00:03:20,057
[400 won cheaper, too...]
3,200 won, going classic.

96
00:03:20,057 --> 00:03:21,060
Sounds good.

97
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:23,056
[Ramyeon: 400 won saved, done]
- How's it? - Looks good.

98
00:03:23,056 --> 00:03:24,497
Alright.

99
00:03:24,497 --> 00:03:27,833
[Next target: lettuce...]

100
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:32,204
[Hunting the cheapest pick, leaf by leaf]

101
00:03:32,204 --> 00:03:33,839
How much is this one?

102
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:36,575
[Treasurer Park stares down the veggies...]

103
00:03:36,575 --> 00:03:38,916
- Perfect with pork belly.
- Yeah.

104
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:40,827
- Just one's enough, right?
- Yeah.

105
00:03:40,827 --> 00:03:43,359
- Instant rice.
- Oh, right, instant rice.

106
00:03:43,359 --> 00:03:45,151
Pricey.

107
00:03:45,151 --> 00:03:47,426
[Ramyeon crew silent over price, round two]

108
00:03:47,426 --> 00:03:49,126
Four for five thousand.

109
00:03:49,126 --> 00:03:51,590
- Should we toss it in?
- Yeah.

110
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:53,059
[5,480 won, must-have rice in the cart]

111
00:03:53,059 --> 00:03:55,078
- Done.
- Done, perfect.

112
00:03:55,078 --> 00:03:56,395
Aren't we getting any drinks?

113
00:03:56,395 --> 00:03:57,878
Let's grab one.

114
00:03:57,878 --> 00:04:00,498
- Hey, Tae Hyung.
- Where is it?

115
00:04:00,498 --> 00:04:03,038
[Everyone doing okay?]
Just go with this one?

116
00:04:03,038 --> 00:04:04,159
- Sure.
- One Coke?

117
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:06,460
[Picking coke with Intern Kim on the label]
- One's fine, right? - Yeah.

118
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:07,679
Tomorrow morning?

119
00:04:07,679 --> 00:04:10,259
Yeah, we should have something for breakfast.

120
00:04:10,259 --> 00:04:12,460
Let's do Spam and fried eggs.

121
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:13,909
- Eggs, then?
- Yeah.

122
00:04:13,909 --> 00:04:16,248
- Eggs and Spam.
- And kimchi.

123
00:04:16,248 --> 00:04:20,193
[Breakfast 101]
Eggs, kimchi, Spam, done.

124
00:04:20,193 --> 00:04:23,608
[Woo Shik's dropping wisdom today]
- Six-pack of eggs? - Just eggs and Spam.

125
00:04:23,608 --> 00:04:25,725
- Light?
- Light's good.

126
00:04:25,725 --> 00:04:27,599
[Picking the lighter ham for breakfast]

127
00:04:27,599 --> 00:04:29,649
[Torn at a 500 won crossroads]
3,300 won? Golden Egg.

128
00:04:29,649 --> 00:04:30,829
Yeah, 3,300 won.

129
00:04:30,829 --> 00:04:32,498
We can splurge 500 won.

130
00:04:32,498 --> 00:04:34,149
- Golden Egg.
- Golden Egg.

131
00:04:34,149 --> 00:04:35,709
- This over that one, right?
- Yeah.

132
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,359
Oh, we can toss this into the Ansungtangmyeon.

133
00:04:37,359 --> 00:04:39,727
- Yeah, that'll work in there.
- Sounds good.

134
00:04:39,727 --> 00:04:41,407
[Hearty eggs cap off the run!]
- Done! - Done!

135
00:04:41,407 --> 00:04:42,775
- Hello.
- Hi.

136
00:04:42,775 --> 00:04:44,426
- Ready to check out?
- Yes.

137
00:04:44,426 --> 00:04:46,045
Could you place your items up here?

138
00:04:46,045 --> 00:04:47,580
[In they go]

139
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:50,149
[Woo Shik sets up a box for packing]

140
00:04:50,149 --> 00:04:52,027
How much did we have left?

141
00:04:52,027 --> 00:04:53,619
140,000 won?

142
00:04:53,619 --> 00:04:55,554
[A little nervous]

143
00:04:55,554 --> 00:04:59,225
[As items start ringing up...]

144
00:04:59,225 --> 00:05:01,393
[The total climbs fast...]

145
00:05:01,393 --> 00:05:04,095
[Eyes locked on the register]

146
00:05:06,026 --> 00:05:07,032
Yes.

147
00:05:07,032 --> 00:05:10,338
[Items stack up neatly in the box...]

148
00:05:10,338 --> 00:05:11,871
No, we won't go over budget.

149
00:05:11,871 --> 00:05:13,618
[Running total: 80,150 won]

150
00:05:13,618 --> 00:05:15,426
We'll have money left over.

151
00:05:15,426 --> 00:05:16,460
- We're good.
- Yeah.

152
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:17,478
[Says it, then fidgets]

153
00:05:17,478 --> 00:05:18,844
Oh, two bottles of water.

154
00:05:18,844 --> 00:05:20,518
[How much did it come to?]

155
00:05:20,518 --> 00:05:22,515
- 91,040 won.
- Okay.

156
00:05:22,515 --> 00:05:23,760
[Penny-pinching pays off, super save]

157
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,384
- We good?
- Yeah.

158
00:05:25,384 --> 00:05:27,118
Here's 100,000 won.

159
00:05:28,493 --> 00:05:30,389
We'll have even more left today.

160
00:05:30,389 --> 00:05:32,062
[Happy]

161
00:05:32,062 --> 00:05:33,618
[Proud]
We saved a bunch, huh?

162
00:05:33,618 --> 00:05:35,859
We saved a ton, seriously? Oh, nice.

163
00:05:35,859 --> 00:05:37,759
We've got over thirty thousand left right now.

164
00:05:37,759 --> 00:05:40,099
[Day 2 holding up strong]
More left than yesterday.

165
00:05:40,099 --> 00:05:41,359
[Expense report: dinner - 91,040 won,
Balance: 39,710 won]

166
00:05:41,359 --> 00:05:43,147
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

167
00:05:43,147 --> 00:05:44,236
Thanks.

168
00:05:44,236 --> 00:05:45,527
[Pocketing the change carefully]

169
00:05:45,527 --> 00:05:47,072
Whoa, it's freezing!

170
00:05:47,072 --> 00:05:50,376
[Cold bodies, warm hearts on the way back]

171
00:05:50,376 --> 00:05:51,259
[Daily rations stowed in the trunk]

172
00:05:51,259 --> 00:05:53,712
- Alright.
- Yes.

173
00:05:53,712 --> 00:05:56,272
[All set, heading to the stay]

174
00:05:56,272 --> 00:05:58,050
- Let's hit the road.
- Yeah.

175
00:05:58,050 --> 00:06:00,420
[Off to the stay, 30 minutes away!]

176
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:02,927
Fun trivia time.

177
00:06:02,927 --> 00:06:04,223
Alright.

178
00:06:04,223 --> 00:06:07,226
How many hearts does an octopus have?

179
00:06:07,226 --> 00:06:08,560
- An octopus's heart?
- Yeah.

180
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,413
- Two.
- Don't they have any?

181
00:06:10,413 --> 00:06:11,430
They have one?

182
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:12,765
Heart...

183
00:06:12,765 --> 00:06:14,827
[Pfft...]

184
00:06:14,827 --> 00:06:16,293
No?

185
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:17,213
Three.

186
00:06:17,213 --> 00:06:18,873
- How come?
- How come?

187
00:06:18,873 --> 00:06:22,141
Two of an octopus's hearts
pump blood to the gills,

188
00:06:22,141 --> 00:06:25,244
and the third pumps blood
through the rest of the body.

189
00:06:25,244 --> 00:06:26,345
[I see...]

190
00:06:26,345 --> 00:06:28,031
- Really?
- And by the way, octopus blood

191
00:06:28,031 --> 00:06:29,793
- has a lot of copper,
- Yeah.

192
00:06:29,793 --> 00:06:31,726
so it's blue.

193
00:06:31,726 --> 00:06:33,033
No way.

194
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,987
Must have great horsepower.

195
00:06:34,987 --> 00:06:37,767
[Woo Shik's Useful Trivia, the End]

196
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:38,848
Whoa, this is Namwon Station.

197
00:06:38,848 --> 00:06:40,759
- It's pretty.
- Looks really unique.

198
00:06:40,759 --> 00:06:43,593
[Hanok-style Namwon Station on the way]

199
00:06:43,593 --> 00:06:46,208
Seo Jun, if there's no car tomorrow,
we'll head to Namwon Station, right?

200
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:48,693
Yeah, Namwon Station it is.

201
00:06:48,693 --> 00:06:50,427
And then off to Boseong?

202
00:06:50,427 --> 00:06:52,471
Yeah.

203
00:06:52,471 --> 00:06:54,808
This is pretty far in.

204
00:06:54,808 --> 00:06:56,688
Man, the bus would have been brutal.

205
00:06:56,688 --> 00:06:58,448
Total disaster, only one bus an hour.

206
00:06:58,448 --> 00:06:59,912
Someone up there is looking out for us.

207
00:06:59,912 --> 00:07:00,893
[Waiting out there with bags? Dizzying...]

208
00:07:00,893 --> 00:07:02,687
Nice.

209
00:07:02,687 --> 00:07:05,375
If we hadn't grabbed the phone today,

210
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:07,887
you couldn't have booked the car-share either,
since it's all on the app.

211
00:07:07,887 --> 00:07:10,159
Right.

212
00:07:10,159 --> 00:07:11,758
This phone really came through.

213
00:07:11,758 --> 00:07:13,915
We'd have been all over the place.

214
00:07:13,915 --> 00:07:16,595
The benefit is huge.

215
00:07:16,595 --> 00:07:17,855
- Right?
- Seriously...

216
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:20,899
- Money left over too, right?
- If it'd been underwear.

217
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:23,102
We even bought pajamas.

218
00:07:23,102 --> 00:07:24,203
Yeah.

219
00:07:24,203 --> 00:07:27,515
[Today in a nutshell]
Super lucky day.

220
00:07:27,515 --> 00:07:29,593
Like, totally...

221
00:07:29,593 --> 00:07:32,244
- Deep in the middle of nowhere.
- Yeah.

222
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:34,513
We're basically off
to do Three Meals a Day right now.

223
00:07:34,513 --> 00:07:35,547
For real.

224
00:07:35,547 --> 00:07:36,882
[Snapping back to reality...]

225
00:07:36,882 --> 00:07:38,918
[Totally different view now...]
We...

226
00:07:38,918 --> 00:07:41,587
Man, if we hadn't had the car...

227
00:07:41,587 --> 00:07:45,391
Feels like a scene out of a movie.

228
00:07:45,391 --> 00:07:46,792
Want to pull over here for a sec?

229
00:07:46,792 --> 00:07:48,828
[Shooting a thriller out here or what?]

230
00:07:48,828 --> 00:07:51,264
There's a Namwon tunnel.

231
00:07:51,264 --> 00:07:52,565
Hey, this is right, isn't it?

232
00:07:52,565 --> 00:07:53,800
Yeah, we're on track.

233
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,694
Let me take a look too.

234
00:07:55,694 --> 00:07:57,954
- Almost there.
- Four kilometers.

235
00:07:57,954 --> 00:07:59,939
Yeah, almost there.

236
00:07:59,939 --> 00:08:02,699
[A thought hits past the tunnel...]

237
00:08:02,699 --> 00:08:05,126
- The crew's in trouble, though.
- What now?

238
00:08:05,126 --> 00:08:07,827
[Worried]
What are they going to do?

239
00:08:07,827 --> 00:08:10,459
[Nothing but open fields all around...]
- There's nothing here. - Nope.

240
00:08:10,459 --> 00:08:11,640
It's not us suffering this time,

241
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,652
the crew's the one in for it.

242
00:08:13,652 --> 00:08:16,992
[Crew's the one walking to the stay today]

243
00:08:16,992 --> 00:08:18,827
- Oktaek Village.
- Huh?

244
00:08:18,827 --> 00:08:21,493
[Pulling into the stay's village]
- Oktaek Village. - Oh, Oktaek Village.

245
00:08:21,493 --> 00:08:25,563
- Feels like the countryside as a kid.
- That's it.

246
00:08:26,832 --> 00:08:30,169
[Quiet village, like grandma's house]

247
00:08:30,169 --> 00:08:33,372
Man, this place would be gorgeous in the snow.

248
00:08:33,372 --> 00:08:34,940
This place has a vibe.

249
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:36,561
We could go for a stroll around the village.

250
00:08:36,561 --> 00:08:38,226
Hey, wouldn't this be
where the bus drops us off?

251
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:39,442
- Yeah.
- That's right.

252
00:08:39,442 --> 00:08:41,161
The bus...

253
00:08:41,161 --> 00:08:42,960
[Bus stop at the village entrance]
Oktaek.

254
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:45,203
- This is it.
- Here we are.

255
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,981
[A village where few houses huddle close]
This place reminds me of my childhood.

256
00:08:49,981 --> 00:08:52,921
[A Hanok tucked deep inside]
Oh, there's a bamboo grove out back.

257
00:08:52,921 --> 00:08:53,959
Hold on.

258
00:08:53,959 --> 00:08:56,576
[Seo Jun hops out first]

259
00:08:57,393 --> 00:08:59,231
Smell the air.

260
00:08:59,231 --> 00:09:01,484
[Starting with the big red gate]

261
00:09:01,484 --> 00:09:05,128
- No way.
- This is insane.

262
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:06,972
We should pull all the way in.

263
00:09:06,972 --> 00:09:09,007
[Calming down and parking up]

264
00:09:12,726 --> 00:09:13,879
[Awestruck by the Hanok's grandeur...]

265
00:09:13,879 --> 00:09:16,415
[And no wonder...]
- What is this? - Crazy, right?

266
00:09:16,415 --> 00:09:18,550
[Following a winding alley]

267
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:21,520
[The Hanok reveals itself like a dream]

268
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:24,646
[Feels like stepping into another world]

269
00:09:24,646 --> 00:09:26,993
Whoa, what is this?

270
00:09:26,993 --> 00:09:29,728
[Heart full, heading to the entrance]
Oh, how cute.

271
00:09:29,728 --> 00:09:33,298
[Following the manual to unlock the door]

272
00:09:33,893 --> 00:09:35,893
[Amazing!]

273
00:09:35,893 --> 00:09:37,760
- This is amazing.
- Inside's great too.

274
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,193
Inside's even better.

275
00:09:40,193 --> 00:09:42,560
[Wonder what's inside...?]

276
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,043
[Switch ON]
Where's the light... oh!

277
00:09:44,043 --> 00:09:47,213
[Lights on, true charm revealed]

278
00:09:47,213 --> 00:09:48,560
Seriously, this is amazing.

279
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,354
- This is total...
- Winter break vibes.

280
00:09:51,354 --> 00:09:52,785
I might just stay right here.

281
00:09:52,785 --> 00:09:54,418
[The perfect winter break spot, revealed]

282
00:09:55,954 --> 00:09:59,170
[Dining table greets you at the door]

283
00:10:00,459 --> 00:10:03,218
[A kitchen begging to be cooked in]

284
00:10:04,129 --> 00:10:07,533
[Leading into a cozy living room]

285
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:12,137
[Inside, the snug main bedroom]

286
00:10:12,137 --> 00:10:15,874
[set to be Po-po's sleep zone]

287
00:10:15,874 --> 00:10:20,045
[Mood-setting decor is a bonus]

288
00:10:20,045 --> 00:10:23,336
[A night in a place where time lingers]

289
00:10:23,336 --> 00:10:24,537
Oh, isn't this pretty?

290
00:10:24,537 --> 00:10:26,017
It's actually beautiful.

291
00:10:26,017 --> 00:10:27,252
So pretty.

292
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:29,126
[But this pretty place
came with one problem...]

293
00:10:29,126 --> 00:10:31,277
My feet are freezing.

294
00:10:31,277 --> 00:10:33,393
It's freezing in here.

295
00:10:33,393 --> 00:10:35,047
[Currently -2 degrees, biting cold]
There's heating here.

296
00:10:35,047 --> 00:10:36,257
Should I try turning it on?

297
00:10:36,257 --> 00:10:39,031
Hello? Hey, we just got here.

298
00:10:39,031 --> 00:10:40,696
[Calling his friend for an urgent SOS]

299
00:10:40,696 --> 00:10:42,026
We unlocked the door and came in,

300
00:10:42,026 --> 00:10:44,837
but my feet are about to turn into ice.
What do we do?

301
00:10:44,837 --> 00:10:45,938
[The two stood frozen in the cold...]

302
00:10:45,938 --> 00:10:47,339
If I go into the room...

303
00:10:47,339 --> 00:10:48,577
[Heat rescuer rushes into the room]

304
00:10:48,577 --> 00:10:50,656
Yeah...

305
00:10:50,656 --> 00:10:55,881
My feet are freezing but it feels so good.

306
00:10:55,881 --> 00:10:57,216
[Happiness blooming in the freezing cold]

307
00:10:57,216 --> 00:11:00,016
- But it's pretty.
- Seriously gorgeous.

308
00:11:00,016 --> 00:11:03,723
It feels kind of like a fridge but I love it.

309
00:11:03,723 --> 00:11:05,224
How is this place so pretty?

310
00:11:05,224 --> 00:11:08,137
Honestly, it was warmer outside
when we walked in, right?

311
00:11:08,137 --> 00:11:10,429
This was basically a freezer.

312
00:11:10,429 --> 00:11:12,277
[To Seo Jun's friend]
We're loving it though.

313
00:11:12,277 --> 00:11:14,700
So warm in here.

314
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,136
Since nobody lives here full-time,

315
00:11:17,136 --> 00:11:19,326
the boiler had been completely off,

316
00:11:19,326 --> 00:11:22,007
and the chill had really settled in.

317
00:11:22,007 --> 00:11:23,526
[A pretty chilly first impression...]

318
00:11:23,526 --> 00:11:26,745
Walking in felt like stepping into a freezer.

319
00:11:26,745 --> 00:11:28,818
I guess this counts as ondol? Feels like ondol.

320
00:11:28,818 --> 00:11:31,197
The boiler panel actually said "ondol" on it.

321
00:11:31,197 --> 00:11:33,752
Yeah, looks like it kicked in.

322
00:11:33,752 --> 00:11:35,387
[The boiler fires up thanks to his friend]
Yeah.

323
00:11:35,387 --> 00:11:37,018
Hey, is it really okay
if we just blast this thing?

324
00:11:37,018 --> 00:11:38,337
It's amazing.

325
00:11:38,337 --> 00:11:39,437
<i>Knock yourself out.</i>

326
00:11:39,437 --> 00:11:40,357
Really?

327
00:11:40,357 --> 00:11:42,895
Oh, you have a security camera out there?

328
00:11:42,895 --> 00:11:45,197
[A camera?]

329
00:11:45,197 --> 00:11:47,667
So your mom's watching us right now.

330
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:50,860
I'll do a bow for the camera.

331
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:52,638
It's outside, right?

332
00:11:52,638 --> 00:11:54,139
- His mom?
- Yeah.

333
00:11:54,139 --> 00:11:55,874
[Can you see us, Mom?]

334
00:11:55,874 --> 00:11:57,509
Thank you so much.

335
00:11:57,509 --> 00:11:59,378
[Quick bow]

336
00:11:59,378 --> 00:12:02,693
[We're grateful too, Mom, the production team]

337
00:12:02,693 --> 00:12:04,593
[Seo Jun was getting the rundown]
Yeah.

338
00:12:04,593 --> 00:12:05,918
Got it.

339
00:12:05,918 --> 00:12:07,593
Thank you.

340
00:12:07,593 --> 00:12:09,259
Yes.

341
00:12:09,259 --> 00:12:11,432
Hold on a second.

342
00:12:11,432 --> 00:12:13,460
Hello. It's Woo Shik.

343
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:16,428
<i>- Ah, yes. I've heard so much about you.</i>
- This is...

344
00:12:16,428 --> 00:12:18,150
About me? Oh, yes.

345
00:12:18,893 --> 00:12:20,652
We're really going
to take good care of this place.

346
00:12:20,652 --> 00:12:23,101
- Thank you.
<i>- Of course. Make yourselves at home.</i>

347
00:12:23,101 --> 00:12:24,912
<i>Treat this place like your own.</i>

348
00:12:24,912 --> 00:12:26,873
It's so beautiful here. Thank you.

349
00:12:26,873 --> 00:12:28,875
<i>Not at all.</i>

350
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:31,092
Anyway, take care.

351
00:12:31,092 --> 00:12:32,712
<i>- Sure.</i>
- And I'll, you know.

352
00:12:32,712 --> 00:12:34,726
<i>- Yeah, you know.</i>
- Right.

353
00:12:34,726 --> 00:12:37,049
- Thanks.
<i>- Right.</i>

354
00:12:37,049 --> 00:12:38,717
[Best friends finishing every sentence
with "you know"]

355
00:12:38,717 --> 00:12:41,860
The boiler works through the whole house,
but he said it takes a while.

356
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:43,488
- Ah, well in that case...
- Yeah.

357
00:12:43,488 --> 00:12:45,249
- You and I can crash outside.
- Sounds good.

358
00:12:45,249 --> 00:12:46,600
No way, what are you talking about?
Forget it.

359
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,909
- No.
- No, I'll sleep there. I'm by myself.

360
00:12:48,909 --> 00:12:49,762
No.

361
00:12:49,762 --> 00:12:52,297
What are we supposed to do about this?

362
00:12:52,297 --> 00:12:53,493
[Paper-screen bathroom]

363
00:12:53,493 --> 00:12:54,549
Why? What's the problem?

364
00:12:54,549 --> 00:12:56,828
It's right there in front.

365
00:12:56,828 --> 00:12:58,804
[Booming voice]
Can you hear me?

366
00:12:58,804 --> 00:13:00,940
[Loud and clear...]

367
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:02,841
I can hear every word.

368
00:13:02,841 --> 00:13:04,959
What about this level?

369
00:13:04,959 --> 00:13:06,593
Yeah, hearing it.

370
00:13:06,593 --> 00:13:07,946
How about this?

371
00:13:07,946 --> 00:13:09,126
Yeah.

372
00:13:09,126 --> 00:13:10,816
I hear it.

373
00:13:10,816 --> 00:13:12,251
[Hit by reality]

374
00:13:12,251 --> 00:13:13,819
Hey, we're in trouble.

375
00:13:13,819 --> 00:13:15,887
[Soundproofing test failed]

376
00:13:15,887 --> 00:13:18,593
But, we're all family here.

377
00:13:18,593 --> 00:13:20,558
I'm fine with it.

378
00:13:23,493 --> 00:13:25,931
We'll all get way closer after this, right?

379
00:13:25,931 --> 00:13:28,501
[That's how you become family...]

380
00:13:28,501 --> 00:13:30,636
So where will you guys sleep?

381
00:13:30,636 --> 00:13:32,976
[Yumi worried about the crew's lodging again]

382
00:13:32,976 --> 00:13:34,908
What about the crew? Where will they sleep?

383
00:13:34,908 --> 00:13:37,432
[Seo Jun worrying outside too...]
Nothing was around when we came in.

384
00:13:37,432 --> 00:13:39,213
They said they called the Village Chief.

385
00:13:39,213 --> 00:13:40,872
Oh really?

386
00:13:40,872 --> 00:13:42,793
But the Village Chief...

387
00:13:42,793 --> 00:13:44,760
Na Yeon, you tell them.

388
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:47,992
The Village Chief said if there's enough room,

389
00:13:47,992 --> 00:13:50,872
he'd let us stay here together.

390
00:13:50,872 --> 00:13:51,831
For real?

391
00:13:51,831 --> 00:13:53,499
Half of us can crash at the village hall,

392
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:54,561
split between men and women.

393
00:13:54,561 --> 00:13:56,962
For real?

394
00:13:56,962 --> 00:13:57,732
[A little earlier]

395
00:13:57,732 --> 00:13:59,509
- For convenience,
- Right.

396
00:13:59,509 --> 00:14:02,046
we already split it
into a men's room and a women's room.

397
00:14:02,046 --> 00:14:04,492
[Village Chief gave the crew the hall]
Oh, close this here.

398
00:14:04,492 --> 00:14:05,971
This part's the men's bathroom now.

399
00:14:05,971 --> 00:14:08,774
[A cozy place to stay, thanks to him]

400
00:14:08,774 --> 00:14:10,243
[Relief]
Thank goodness.

401
00:14:10,243 --> 00:14:13,044
[Everyone just felt grateful]
Honestly, there was nothing on the way in.

402
00:14:13,912 --> 00:14:16,648
[Worry off, dinner prep starts...]

403
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:19,626
Huh? No water's coming out.

404
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:21,253
Oh, it must've frozen.

405
00:14:21,253 --> 00:14:23,121
[Then came a real problem...]

406
00:14:23,121 --> 00:14:24,590
[SOS round two]

407
00:14:24,590 --> 00:14:27,292
He said there's a valve
on the water meter outside

408
00:14:27,292 --> 00:14:29,400
that you have to open.

409
00:14:30,326 --> 00:14:31,430
Hold on.

410
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:33,419
[Not frozen after all, thankfully]

411
00:14:33,419 --> 00:14:34,555
To the right?

412
00:14:34,555 --> 00:14:35,802
- Oh, here it is.
- Oh, is this it?

413
00:14:35,802 --> 00:14:38,470
[Heading behind the main gate...]
Like a plastic thing?

414
00:14:38,470 --> 00:14:39,234
[Past 7 PM and pitch dark already]

415
00:14:39,234 --> 00:14:40,238
Yeah.

416
00:14:40,238 --> 00:14:41,374
[Flashlight ON]

417
00:14:41,374 --> 00:14:42,841
Yeah.

418
00:14:42,841 --> 00:14:44,876
If I open it, is this the valve?

419
00:14:44,876 --> 00:14:47,387
[Mission: Find the valve!]

420
00:14:47,387 --> 00:14:49,793
[But the valve was nowhere in sight]

421
00:14:49,793 --> 00:14:51,041
Hold on a sec.

422
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:53,785
Is it the thing with the hose

423
00:14:53,785 --> 00:14:56,361
right here?

424
00:14:56,361 --> 00:14:59,426
<i>No, it's buried in the ground.</i>

425
00:14:59,426 --> 00:15:01,341
[Phone call wasn't cutting it...]
Like a jar stand?

426
00:15:01,341 --> 00:15:03,995
Hold on. Let me video call you.

427
00:15:05,297 --> 00:15:08,400
[Video support brought in too]

428
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,641
Is this it?

429
00:15:09,641 --> 00:15:10,701
<i>Yeah.</i>

430
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:11,841
<i>Hold on a sec,</i>

431
00:15:11,841 --> 00:15:13,775
<i>open that one too.</i>

432
00:15:13,775 --> 00:15:15,441
[Lifting the cover as he said]
<i>Open that one too.</i>

433
00:15:15,441 --> 00:15:16,781
Yeah.

434
00:15:16,781 --> 00:15:17,962
<i>Crack that one open too.</i>

435
00:15:17,962 --> 00:15:19,181
I have to open this too?

436
00:15:19,181 --> 00:15:20,212
<i>Yeah.</i>

437
00:15:20,212 --> 00:15:22,048
[Like nesting dolls...]

438
00:15:22,048 --> 00:15:24,026
So I turn this?

439
00:15:24,026 --> 00:15:25,484
<i>Yeah.</i>

440
00:15:25,484 --> 00:15:28,364
[The valve finally revealed]
<i>Apparently someone locked it. No clue why.</i>

441
00:15:28,364 --> 00:15:29,924
Got it.

442
00:15:29,924 --> 00:15:32,305
<i>- Feel any water coming through?</i>
- Yeah, it's flowing. I can hear it.

443
00:15:32,305 --> 00:15:33,893
Got it.

444
00:15:33,893 --> 00:15:36,695
[Sign of success]
I can hear shouting from over there.

445
00:15:36,695 --> 00:15:38,864
[Yumi was prepping in the kitchen...]

446
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:45,044
[Heading to the bathroom
at the sound of rushing water]

447
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:47,173
It's fun.

448
00:15:47,173 --> 00:15:49,575
<i>Yeah, enjoy yourself.</i>

449
00:15:49,575 --> 00:15:52,314
[Anyway, thanks again]
- Okay. <i>- Yeah.</i>

450
00:15:52,314 --> 00:15:54,279
Hearing her react like that right away...

451
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:56,013
[Sensed success]

452
00:15:56,013 --> 00:15:57,026
[Everything back in place]

453
00:15:57,026 --> 00:15:58,884
Okay.

454
00:15:58,884 --> 00:16:01,609
[Mission complete, heading back]

455
00:16:01,609 --> 00:16:04,122
- Water working?
- Yeah, it's running.

456
00:16:05,056 --> 00:16:08,293
[Water's flowing, so dinner prep kicks in]

457
00:16:08,293 --> 00:16:12,130
[Setting up the grill for the meat first]

458
00:16:13,466 --> 00:16:15,967
Hey, this kimchi is incredible.

459
00:16:16,902 --> 00:16:20,065
[Namwon Brother's kimchi gift arrives]

460
00:16:21,006 --> 00:16:24,488
[Sparkling]

461
00:16:26,612 --> 00:16:29,314
Oh my goodness.

462
00:16:29,314 --> 00:16:32,617
[Scoop out just enough kimchi]

463
00:16:32,617 --> 00:16:35,691
[Container goes back where it was]

464
00:16:35,691 --> 00:16:37,400
What should we grill first?

465
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,741
How about pork belly?

466
00:16:38,741 --> 00:16:40,040
Okay.

467
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,521
Pork belly, pork neck,
then thin-sliced after that?

468
00:16:42,521 --> 00:16:43,900
Okay.

469
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,241
Or we could turn this into kimchi stew.

470
00:16:46,241 --> 00:16:48,066
- Sounds good.
- Pork neck it is.

471
00:16:48,066 --> 00:16:51,837
[Kimchi stew chef rolls up his sleeves]
It's pretty simple to throw together.

472
00:16:51,837 --> 00:16:54,867
[Woo Shik prepping the veggies]

473
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,476
[Ting]

474
00:16:57,476 --> 00:16:59,744
[Yumi sends the ssamjang flying...]

475
00:16:59,744 --> 00:17:01,513
[Yikes...]

476
00:17:01,513 --> 00:17:03,916
Whew, that was close.

477
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:05,317
There are paper towels here.

478
00:17:05,317 --> 00:17:06,811
[Saved the ssamjang just in time]

479
00:17:06,811 --> 00:17:09,120
Whew, lucky the lid was on.

480
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:10,936
[Wipes up the spilled ssamjang]

481
00:17:11,858 --> 00:17:13,959
[Smell check too...]
No smell at all.

482
00:17:13,959 --> 00:17:16,561
[Chef Park starts on the kimchi stew]

483
00:17:16,561 --> 00:17:19,064
[Seo Jun's kimchi stew recipe
1. Slice the pork neck]

484
00:17:19,064 --> 00:17:22,501
[2. Add pork belly]

485
00:17:22,501 --> 00:17:28,039
[3. Stir-fry the meat]

486
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:31,726
[4. Cut the kimchi]

487
00:17:31,726 --> 00:17:33,646
This is going to hit just right.

488
00:17:33,646 --> 00:17:36,414
[Kimchi looks so good, confidence rising]
Real legit stuff.

489
00:17:37,482 --> 00:17:41,285
[5. Stir-fry the kimchi too]

490
00:17:43,855 --> 00:17:47,199
[Woo Shik busy setting the table]

491
00:17:48,008 --> 00:17:50,059
- Got the garlic out?
- Yeah.

492
00:17:50,059 --> 00:17:51,663
Need to chop some garlic.

493
00:17:51,663 --> 00:17:53,992
Let's throw garlic in the kimchi stew.

494
00:17:53,992 --> 00:17:55,767
Then I should slice it up first.

495
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:58,236
[Getting ready to chop]

496
00:17:58,236 --> 00:18:02,440
[Lying down a newspaper for the oil splatter]

497
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:05,143
[Setup done, camera ON]

498
00:18:05,143 --> 00:18:07,045
How much garlic do you want?

499
00:18:07,045 --> 00:18:08,779
Garlic?

500
00:18:10,683 --> 00:18:12,817
About three cloves?

501
00:18:16,421 --> 00:18:20,966
[6. Add the garlic Yumi sliced]

502
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:24,796
[Prep work finished]

503
00:18:24,796 --> 00:18:27,927
[Grilling begins]

504
00:18:27,927 --> 00:18:29,786
What's that smell? It's amazing.

505
00:18:29,786 --> 00:18:32,436
- The kimchi must be really good.
- Right now...

506
00:18:33,638 --> 00:18:35,608
[Delicious aroma filling the house]

507
00:18:35,608 --> 00:18:39,778
This kimchi must be something else.

508
00:18:39,778 --> 00:18:41,546
[Pop one in]

509
00:18:41,546 --> 00:18:43,281
- Whoa.
- What?

510
00:18:43,281 --> 00:18:44,849
This kimchi is so good.

511
00:18:44,849 --> 00:18:46,685
- You tried it?
- Whoa.

512
00:18:46,685 --> 00:18:48,087
- This is...
- That good?

513
00:18:48,087 --> 00:18:49,920
So good.

514
00:18:51,693 --> 00:18:55,427
The stew won't even need anything extra.

515
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:57,796
[Pours water into the pot, just enough]

516
00:18:57,796 --> 00:19:00,031
[Seasons it]

517
00:19:00,031 --> 00:19:03,336
[Let it simmer slowly]

518
00:19:03,336 --> 00:19:04,669
Whoa, so good.

519
00:19:04,669 --> 00:19:06,882
[Pork belly goes on the grill]

520
00:19:06,882 --> 00:19:09,507
Meat duty.

521
00:19:09,507 --> 00:19:11,809
- Scissors?
- Scissors.

522
00:19:12,582 --> 00:19:13,982
Two bowls of rice?

523
00:19:13,982 --> 00:19:15,143
- Rice...
- Two for now.

524
00:19:15,143 --> 00:19:18,126
- Two.
- Two for now.

525
00:19:18,126 --> 00:19:21,193
<i>♪ La-la-la-la-la ♪</i>

526
00:19:21,193 --> 00:19:24,911
[Singing comes naturally for meat duty]

527
00:19:26,101 --> 00:19:27,859
This place has one drawback.

528
00:19:27,859 --> 00:19:29,262
Huh? Me? Over there?

529
00:19:29,262 --> 00:19:31,796
My head's hitting it.

530
00:19:31,796 --> 00:19:34,566
[Facing the wall]

531
00:19:34,566 --> 00:19:38,203
[Under the meat duty's command]

532
00:19:38,203 --> 00:19:41,505
[Pork belly turning golden]

533
00:19:42,776 --> 00:19:45,643
Looks delicious.

534
00:19:46,778 --> 00:19:48,057
Should I try one?

535
00:19:48,057 --> 00:19:49,549
I'll give it a taste first.

536
00:19:49,549 --> 00:19:51,182
Yeah.

537
00:19:51,182 --> 00:19:53,585
[Dips it in ssamjang]

538
00:19:53,585 --> 00:19:55,994
[Eldest Yumi gets the first piece]

539
00:19:59,691 --> 00:20:01,476
Eat it quickly.

540
00:20:01,476 --> 00:20:03,795
It's amazing.

541
00:20:03,795 --> 00:20:04,836
This one.

542
00:20:04,836 --> 00:20:07,293
[Woo Shik hands a piece to Seo Jun]
Yeah, here.

543
00:20:07,293 --> 00:20:10,802
[Makes a wrap right away]

544
00:20:10,802 --> 00:20:13,090
[Loads it up with garlic and green onion]

545
00:20:14,272 --> 00:20:16,675
[Folds it neatly, hands it to Woo Shik]

546
00:20:18,860 --> 00:20:20,678
Have one of these.

547
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:24,305
[Yumi taking care of him again]

548
00:20:24,305 --> 00:20:27,212
Hey, do you always cut meat this small?

549
00:20:27,212 --> 00:20:29,956
I do cut it kind of small.

550
00:20:29,956 --> 00:20:31,072
Really?

551
00:20:31,072 --> 00:20:33,825
- Got a small mouth maybe?
- Yeah.

552
00:20:33,825 --> 00:20:36,996
[Mine's big though]

553
00:20:36,996 --> 00:20:39,163
[Nods]
- Tasty. - Yeah.

554
00:20:40,793 --> 00:20:42,600
Garlic.

555
00:20:44,302 --> 00:20:48,339
Never thought
we'd have a party like this today.

556
00:20:50,508 --> 00:20:53,244
[Moved]

557
00:20:53,244 --> 00:20:56,647
[Stuffing it into a small mouth]

558
00:20:58,259 --> 00:20:59,617
Seriously delicious.

559
00:20:59,617 --> 00:21:01,419
[Chopsticks flying]

560
00:21:06,927 --> 00:21:09,193
Try it with rice, it's amazing.

561
00:21:09,961 --> 00:21:12,130
[Nothing but reactions all around]

562
00:21:14,896 --> 00:21:17,836
Hey, thanks so much.

563
00:21:17,836 --> 00:21:20,037
Thanks, Joong Hyun.

564
00:21:22,259 --> 00:21:24,208
Thank you.

565
00:21:25,726 --> 00:21:28,113
About tomorrow,

566
00:21:28,113 --> 00:21:30,748
are you going
with what we talked about at the cafe?

567
00:21:30,748 --> 00:21:32,917
[About that cafe earlier...]
Yeah.

568
00:21:32,917 --> 00:21:36,312
[They actually stopped
by a cafe before grocery shopping]

569
00:21:36,312 --> 00:21:38,723
- Hey, what if we get the car tomorrow...
- Yeah.

570
00:21:38,723 --> 00:21:40,757
Then we should jump pretty far tomorrow.

571
00:21:40,757 --> 00:21:42,093
- Right.
- Right, while we have it.

572
00:21:42,093 --> 00:21:44,059
- Boseong would be a waste of our benefit.
- Yeah.

573
00:21:44,059 --> 00:21:45,830
So then...

574
00:21:46,587 --> 00:21:48,133
Yeongdeok?

575
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:52,426
[Driving from Namwon to Yeongdeok
takes three hours]

576
00:21:52,426 --> 00:21:54,038
If we get the car?

577
00:21:54,038 --> 00:21:55,768
Then straight to Yeongdeok.

578
00:21:55,768 --> 00:21:57,827
Then we'd move the next day.

579
00:21:57,827 --> 00:22:00,068
We'd take the train to Samcheok then.

580
00:22:00,068 --> 00:22:02,628
- Gorgeous coastal views
- Sounds great.

581
00:22:02,628 --> 00:22:03,868
on the Mugunghwa.

582
00:22:03,868 --> 00:22:06,388
If we get the car tomorrow,
should we head to Yeongdeok?

583
00:22:06,388 --> 00:22:08,487
- Let's do it.
- Then here's the plan.

584
00:22:08,487 --> 00:22:11,059
- Car in Namwon, Yeongdeok.
- Yeah.

585
00:22:11,059 --> 00:22:13,759
- No car in Namwon, Boseong.
- Yeah.

586
00:22:13,759 --> 00:22:17,317
- Car in Boseong, Yeongdeok.
- Yeongdeok.

587
00:22:17,317 --> 00:22:19,159
- And...
- If we get the car, Yeongdeok no matter what.

588
00:22:19,159 --> 00:22:20,992
If the car comes up...

589
00:22:20,992 --> 00:22:23,034
Yeongdeok.

590
00:22:23,034 --> 00:22:24,917
Hope the car comes up for real.

591
00:22:24,917 --> 00:22:27,657
Cars come with GPS built in.

592
00:22:27,657 --> 00:22:29,578
Just punch it in and head to Yeongdeok.

593
00:22:29,578 --> 00:22:32,493
For tomorrow, I'd love the car.

594
00:22:32,493 --> 00:22:34,257
- I'd love the car too.
- Same here.

595
00:22:34,257 --> 00:22:36,281
That's the first choice.

596
00:22:36,281 --> 00:22:39,894
[Second choice, we'll talk after eating]

597
00:22:39,894 --> 00:22:43,378
But lodging could be nice too.

598
00:22:43,378 --> 00:22:45,656
- Anything works really.
- Yeah.

599
00:22:46,679 --> 00:22:49,527
I used the phone today,
so I think I could pass it on.

600
00:22:49,527 --> 00:22:51,426
Yeah.

601
00:22:51,426 --> 00:22:54,379
We're hitting the coast tomorrow
no matter what, right?

602
00:22:54,379 --> 00:22:57,339
- Beach no matter where.
- We should see the ocean.

603
00:22:57,339 --> 00:23:00,240
- A place by the beach won't come cheap.
- Yeah, true.

604
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:04,141
- Tons of guesthouses by the water, right?
- Right.

605
00:23:05,385 --> 00:23:07,178
So we just found a guesthouse by the shore.

606
00:23:07,178 --> 00:23:08,938
- Honestly, a guesthouse sounds nice.
- Yeah.

607
00:23:08,938 --> 00:23:10,381
A guesthouse for one night.

608
00:23:10,381 --> 00:23:11,460
[A satisfied clink]

609
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:13,384
Yeah.

610
00:23:18,489 --> 00:23:22,160
[Kimchi stew bubbling away]

611
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:24,685
[Seo Jun's kimchi stew is finally ready]

612
00:23:27,793 --> 00:23:29,500
- This is going to be good.
- Yeah.

613
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:30,893
[Scooping a bowl loaded with goodies]

614
00:23:30,893 --> 00:23:32,337
Thanks.

615
00:23:32,337 --> 00:23:34,255
[Yumi gets the first taste, as always]

616
00:23:38,592 --> 00:23:41,279
Tastes like tuna. Like there's tuna in here.

617
00:23:41,279 --> 00:23:42,426
[Hahaha]

618
00:23:42,426 --> 00:23:44,782
Did you sneak fish in there on us?

619
00:23:44,782 --> 00:23:46,417
[Slurp]

620
00:23:46,417 --> 00:23:47,077
[Smack]

621
00:23:47,077 --> 00:23:49,658
- See? Tuna, right?
- I'm getting a spicy seafood stew vibe.

622
00:23:49,658 --> 00:23:50,738
I taste tuna.

623
00:23:50,738 --> 00:23:52,626
- The flavor's deep. Like really deep.
- Deep.

624
00:23:52,626 --> 00:23:54,393
It's good.

625
00:23:54,393 --> 00:23:58,692
[A spicy, refreshing,
deep-flavored kimchi stew]

626
00:24:00,465 --> 00:24:03,001
[Cleansing the palate with that sharp broth]

627
00:24:03,001 --> 00:24:05,235
How is this so sharp and spicy?

628
00:24:06,104 --> 00:24:09,306
We totally lucked out today, didn't we?

629
00:24:10,293 --> 00:24:12,844
Setting aside every other possibility,

630
00:24:12,844 --> 00:24:16,047
we still need to leave
on the original Boseong schedule.

631
00:24:16,047 --> 00:24:17,750
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

632
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:20,927
The train was at 10:37 AM or something.

633
00:24:20,927 --> 00:24:22,664
We've got to get up early.

634
00:24:22,664 --> 00:24:23,905
Huh? 10:30...

635
00:24:23,905 --> 00:24:24,965
What was it?

636
00:24:24,965 --> 00:24:26,385
[Actual departure time: 10:47 AM]
10:30?

637
00:24:26,385 --> 00:24:28,544
10:37?

638
00:24:28,544 --> 00:24:31,564
- That's early. Tomorrow's an early one.
- Yeah.

639
00:24:31,564 --> 00:24:34,232
So we're looking at hitting the road by nine?

640
00:24:34,232 --> 00:24:36,434
- We're catching it at Namwon Station, right?
- Yeah.

641
00:24:36,434 --> 00:24:38,226
We've got to be out by nine.

642
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:40,104
In that case...

643
00:24:40,693 --> 00:24:44,284
[Mapping route to Namwon Station]
From back there to Namwon Station?

644
00:24:44,284 --> 00:24:47,284
It's not that far from there to Namwon Station.

645
00:24:47,284 --> 00:24:49,404
[Since it's close]
Let's just grab a cab.

646
00:24:49,404 --> 00:24:51,976
We saved a ton of cash today.

647
00:24:51,976 --> 00:24:54,860
Last night too, and tonight,

648
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:56,132
things feel amazing right now,

649
00:24:56,132 --> 00:24:58,660
but when I think about tomorrow, I get nervous.

650
00:24:58,660 --> 00:25:00,526
Come on, what's there to stress about?

651
00:25:00,526 --> 00:25:03,293
We'll worry about tomorrow when tomorrow comes.

652
00:25:04,476 --> 00:25:07,133
Honestly...

653
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:09,268
- to be real with you,
- Yeah.

654
00:25:09,268 --> 00:25:11,669
I'm so happy right now. For real.

655
00:25:11,669 --> 00:25:14,059
[Getting all sentimental]

656
00:25:14,059 --> 00:25:16,157
- Ah, this is nice.
- Really nice.

657
00:25:16,157 --> 00:25:18,511
- I could live like this forever.
- Huh?

658
00:25:18,511 --> 00:25:22,547
[Leaving teary Woo Shik behind]
Hey, coming here was the best call ever.

659
00:25:22,547 --> 00:25:23,781
[Boiling ramyeon for dessert]

660
00:25:23,781 --> 00:25:25,034
Here it is.

661
00:25:25,034 --> 00:25:27,015
So do we just haul the eggs around tomorrow?

662
00:25:27,015 --> 00:25:28,815
Should we boil what's left?

663
00:25:28,815 --> 00:25:31,359
Hey, boil them and we'll bring them.

664
00:25:31,359 --> 00:25:33,954
- We can eat them on the train.
- Yeah, let's do it.

665
00:25:33,954 --> 00:25:35,493
Boil what's left. Let's boil them.

666
00:25:35,493 --> 00:25:37,328
[Meal ends on a boiled-egg plan...]

667
00:25:37,328 --> 00:25:39,554
I'll handle the dishes.

668
00:25:39,554 --> 00:25:40,615
Hang on,

669
00:25:40,615 --> 00:25:41,793
- I'm just borrowing this real quick.
- Sure.

670
00:25:41,793 --> 00:25:44,068
[Borrowing Seo Jun's hat]
My bangs keep getting in the way.

671
00:25:44,068 --> 00:25:47,338
[Checks himself out in the bathroom]

672
00:25:47,338 --> 00:25:49,976
[Seo Jun pulls on the rubber gloves]

673
00:25:49,976 --> 00:25:51,560
[Peek]

674
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:53,279
While you're in there, just wash up.

675
00:25:53,279 --> 00:25:54,860
- Huh?
- Shower and come out.

676
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:56,560
By the time I'm done,
there won't be any dishes left.

677
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:58,760
No, there's still plenty here.

678
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,127
- Just go wash up.
- Hey, I've got it!

679
00:26:00,127 --> 00:26:01,346
I'll do it!

680
00:26:01,346 --> 00:26:02,907
[They fight to do the dishes...]
You shower first!

681
00:26:02,907 --> 00:26:05,423
There's other stuff to do too, you know.

682
00:26:05,423 --> 00:26:07,425
[In the end...]

683
00:26:07,425 --> 00:26:11,696
[Shower, tidy up, then dishes]

684
00:26:11,696 --> 00:26:13,667
Hey, the floor's seriously
toasty in here now, huh?

685
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:15,626
Right? Isn't it getting too hot?

686
00:26:15,626 --> 00:26:17,393
Should I turn it down?

687
00:26:17,393 --> 00:26:19,760
- Won't catch fire, will it?
- Exactly.

688
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,326
I think turning it down should do it.

689
00:26:21,326 --> 00:26:23,241
Yeah, it's seriously hot.

690
00:26:23,241 --> 00:26:24,893
[The house turned scorching hot]

691
00:26:24,893 --> 00:26:26,911
Hold on, this...

692
00:26:26,911 --> 00:26:29,180
[A seriously hunched back]

693
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:30,982
- Hey, I'll take over.
- Huh?

694
00:26:30,982 --> 00:26:34,052
Better me than you bending over like that.

695
00:26:34,052 --> 00:26:36,323
[Dish duty changes hands]

696
00:26:36,323 --> 00:26:38,497
I'm the perfect height.

697
00:26:39,126 --> 00:26:41,959
- Your head really doesn't hit?
- Not even close.

698
00:26:42,627 --> 00:26:45,905
[Fresh PJs on a clean Woo Shik]

699
00:26:45,905 --> 00:26:47,983
- This is hilarious.
- What?

700
00:26:47,983 --> 00:26:49,026
[Woo Shik in his cute outfit]

701
00:26:49,026 --> 00:26:50,968
Oh, the PJs.

702
00:26:51,803 --> 00:26:55,875
[Heads to Yumi at the sink]

703
00:26:55,875 --> 00:26:57,176
- I'll take over.
- Here...

704
00:26:57,176 --> 00:27:02,013
- you grab a paper towel and dry these off.
- Got it.

705
00:27:02,013 --> 00:27:04,342
[Order received]

706
00:27:05,383 --> 00:27:09,554
[Carrying out the mission]

707
00:27:09,554 --> 00:27:14,158
[Even tidies up the trash]

708
00:27:15,059 --> 00:27:18,898
[Yumi finishes up the dishes]

709
00:27:18,898 --> 00:27:20,598
We've got to hit the sack soon.

710
00:27:20,598 --> 00:27:22,226
Want me to kill the lights?

711
00:27:23,101 --> 00:27:24,827
[Two side by side in matching PJs]

712
00:27:24,827 --> 00:27:26,537
[Bolts up]
How do we turn off the lights in here?

713
00:27:26,537 --> 00:27:28,372
[Looking around]
The light...

714
00:27:28,372 --> 00:27:29,593
[Everyone goes full meerkat]

715
00:27:29,593 --> 00:27:30,747
Over there...

716
00:27:30,747 --> 00:27:32,419
There it is!

717
00:27:33,059 --> 00:27:34,293
I'll go ahead and stick it.

718
00:27:34,293 --> 00:27:36,493
- "Stick it," I say.
- Go ahead, stick it.

719
00:27:36,493 --> 00:27:38,682
- Stick it.
- I'll shut it off.

720
00:27:39,893 --> 00:27:41,085
This one first.

721
00:27:41,085 --> 00:27:41,927
[Lights go out one by one]

722
00:27:41,927 --> 00:27:43,660
- Does that do it?
- Yeah.

723
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:46,092
- Okay.
- Not bad.

724
00:27:46,092 --> 00:27:47,553
Hang on.

725
00:27:47,553 --> 00:27:49,327
[Click]
What does this switch do?

726
00:27:49,327 --> 00:27:51,267
[It's me...]
Outside, maybe?

727
00:27:52,593 --> 00:27:53,526
[Found it]
Yeah, it's outside.

728
00:27:53,526 --> 00:27:55,299
- Cool if I cut the light?
- Yeah.

729
00:27:55,299 --> 00:27:56,726
[Lights finally out]
- Huh? - Lights out?

730
00:27:56,726 --> 00:27:59,360
What do I do?
Can you leave just the middle one on?

731
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:02,059
[Wait, I haven't gotten ready for bed]
- I can see fine. - No, I...

732
00:28:02,059 --> 00:28:04,626
I still have to move around.
I haven't changed yet.

733
00:28:04,626 --> 00:28:07,626
The middle light you just shut off,
which one was it?

734
00:28:07,626 --> 00:28:09,920
- This is the one I shut off.
- It's fine!

735
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:10,848
I'll kill this one instead!

736
00:28:10,848 --> 00:28:12,316
- Yeah, do it!
- Hang on, I...

737
00:28:12,316 --> 00:28:14,051
I can see this one too!

738
00:28:14,051 --> 00:28:16,026
It's not about whether I can see,

739
00:28:16,026 --> 00:28:17,992
I've got to come out and move around first.

740
00:28:17,992 --> 00:28:19,590
How do you shut this one off?

741
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:20,691
That one?

742
00:28:20,691 --> 00:28:21,859
[Another light catches Yumi's eye]

743
00:28:21,859 --> 00:28:23,661
- Should I leave it on?
- No!

744
00:28:23,661 --> 00:28:25,337
I'll figure that one out.

745
00:28:25,337 --> 00:28:26,957
Get ready to turn in.

746
00:28:26,957 --> 00:28:28,835
- Got it.
- Yeah.

747
00:28:28,835 --> 00:28:29,838
[Yumi's knee]
[Pop]

748
00:28:29,838 --> 00:28:31,277
It's popping now.

749
00:28:31,277 --> 00:28:33,276
Yeah, popping is fine.

750
00:28:33,276 --> 00:28:35,505
[Random words]
It pops on its own anyway.

751
00:28:36,607 --> 00:28:39,545
[Woo Shik takes round two of lights-out]

752
00:28:39,545 --> 00:28:42,079
Where do I turn this thing off?

753
00:28:42,815 --> 00:28:44,971
Isn't it inside somewhere?

754
00:28:46,152 --> 00:28:47,817
[Lights ON again]
Ugh, my stomach.

755
00:28:47,817 --> 00:28:49,255
[Woo Shik drops a midnight beat]

756
00:28:49,255 --> 00:28:50,938
Oh, man.

757
00:28:50,938 --> 00:28:53,339
Didn't you turn this one on earlier?

758
00:28:53,339 --> 00:28:56,360
Could it be inside, like over on the left?

759
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:58,362
[Searching every inch]

760
00:28:58,362 --> 00:29:00,431
[Mind-blowing]
- Can't find it. - Nothing?

761
00:29:00,431 --> 00:29:02,226
[Light's on, but no switch in sight]

762
00:29:02,226 --> 00:29:03,801
Who flipped this one on earlier?

763
00:29:03,801 --> 00:29:04,804
[Found it]

764
00:29:04,804 --> 00:29:06,837
[Mission finally accomplished]

765
00:29:06,837 --> 00:29:09,359
[Bedtime for real now]

766
00:29:09,359 --> 00:29:10,600
- Hold up.
- Right.

767
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,578
No picking your nose in your sleep.

768
00:29:12,578 --> 00:29:14,847
- Hey, hold on.
- If you fart in your sleep,

769
00:29:14,847 --> 00:29:16,799
we're all going to hear it.

770
00:29:16,799 --> 00:29:19,017
[They roast her nonstop]
You know what, I'm shutting this off.

771
00:29:19,017 --> 00:29:20,119
Don't kill it.

772
00:29:20,119 --> 00:29:22,827
I'll shower real quick and come right out.

773
00:29:22,827 --> 00:29:24,092
You're washing just your back and coming out?

774
00:29:24,092 --> 00:29:26,526
- A quick wash.
- Ah, quick.

775
00:29:26,526 --> 00:29:29,396
I was going to ask
why you're only washing your back.

776
00:29:29,396 --> 00:29:31,629
I thought you literally meant just your back.

777
00:29:31,629 --> 00:29:33,660
[Yumi heads off to wash up]

778
00:29:33,660 --> 00:29:35,733
It's all soaked.

779
00:29:35,733 --> 00:29:36,936
[Startled]
I can't see.

780
00:29:36,936 --> 00:29:38,593
- I said it's all wet.
- I see.

781
00:29:38,593 --> 00:29:40,957
[They're...]
Bathrooms get wet like that sometimes.

782
00:29:40,957 --> 00:29:42,259
[in sync]
It'll probably all get wet.

783
00:29:42,259 --> 00:29:43,860
I'll just take my socks off.

784
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,910
[They're...]
Yeah, socks come off before you go in.

785
00:29:45,910 --> 00:29:48,312
[in sync]
Yeah, you'll probably have to take them off.

786
00:29:48,312 --> 00:29:49,680
Yeah.

787
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,626
[Socks off, ready to wash up]

788
00:29:50,626 --> 00:29:53,159
Hey, that's risky.

789
00:29:53,159 --> 00:29:54,537
Let's do another round.

790
00:29:54,537 --> 00:29:56,354
I'm hitting the sack now.

791
00:29:56,354 --> 00:29:58,456
[Mirror image]

792
00:29:58,456 --> 00:29:59,890
- Seo Jun.
- Yeah?

793
00:29:59,890 --> 00:30:01,558
You asleep?

794
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:04,603
[Looks back subtly]

795
00:30:04,603 --> 00:30:06,865
[Staring]

796
00:30:06,865 --> 00:30:08,460
[Laughing]

797
00:30:08,460 --> 00:30:11,223
- What?
- Why are you smiling in your sleep?

798
00:30:11,223 --> 00:30:12,755
I wasn't smiling though?

799
00:30:12,755 --> 00:30:14,313
But you are smiling?

800
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:16,789
I'm sleeping, what are you talking about?

801
00:30:16,789 --> 00:30:18,618
Ah, man...

802
00:30:18,618 --> 00:30:21,118
You must've been having a really nice dream.

803
00:30:22,446 --> 00:30:24,815
[Woo Shik suddenly jumps up]

804
00:30:24,815 --> 00:30:26,452
[Digging through the Daiso paper bag]

805
00:30:26,452 --> 00:30:28,159
[Glances around]

806
00:30:28,159 --> 00:30:30,001
What are you doing?

807
00:30:30,706 --> 00:30:33,569
What, putting in earplugs again?

808
00:30:33,569 --> 00:30:36,994
[Trying out the must-have item
bought earlier at Daiso]

809
00:30:36,994 --> 00:30:40,285
[Falling asleep hoping for 1,000 won
worth of happiness]

810
00:30:41,052 --> 00:30:46,160
[Another day in Namwon comes to an end]

811
00:30:48,313 --> 00:30:49,707
[Yawn]

812
00:30:49,707 --> 00:30:52,580
[Waking up in the morning with a stretch]

813
00:30:52,580 --> 00:30:54,516
[Yawn]

814
00:30:54,516 --> 00:30:59,249
[Putting away the dishes dried overnight]

815
00:30:59,249 --> 00:31:00,902
Oh, dear.

816
00:31:00,902 --> 00:31:02,353
Oh.

817
00:31:02,353 --> 00:31:04,574
[Humming a lively tune]

818
00:31:04,574 --> 00:31:05,787
Oh, oh.

819
00:31:05,787 --> 00:31:09,060
[While Woo Shik noisily goes to wash up]

820
00:31:09,060 --> 00:31:13,453
[Seo Jun finishes tidying the dishes]

821
00:31:13,453 --> 00:31:17,713
[And neatly folds up the bedding too]

822
00:31:17,713 --> 00:31:22,368
[Next task: Boil water]

823
00:31:25,169 --> 00:31:30,130
[Using the water Seo Jun put on]

824
00:31:30,130 --> 00:31:31,836
[Woo Shik, freshly washed up, boils some eggs]

825
00:31:32,932 --> 00:31:36,590
[Meanwhile, Yumi dries her hair]

826
00:31:37,469 --> 00:31:40,026
Wow. It's already dry.

827
00:31:41,045 --> 00:31:43,556
It's lighter than the one I used before.

828
00:31:45,691 --> 00:31:47,265
But is it really light, though?

829
00:31:47,265 --> 00:31:49,069
This is really light.

830
00:31:49,069 --> 00:31:51,844
Oh, well... I think I might buy one.

831
00:31:51,844 --> 00:31:53,390
You can take that with you.

832
00:31:53,390 --> 00:31:55,840
Oh, really? Yay!

833
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,836
[Rolling]
Am I really taking this with me?

834
00:31:57,836 --> 00:31:58,876
Yes, you can take it.

835
00:31:58,876 --> 00:32:01,312
[A travel gift prepared
by the production staff]

836
00:32:01,312 --> 00:32:02,701
Let's put it in for now.

837
00:32:02,701 --> 00:32:05,204
It fits perfectly in the bag.

838
00:32:05,204 --> 00:32:08,006
[Yumi is ready too]

839
00:32:12,050 --> 00:32:15,300
[Fits neatly into the pouch]

840
00:32:16,036 --> 00:32:19,670
[The matching pajamas bought in Daegu too]

841
00:32:19,670 --> 00:32:21,627
[Slip right into the paper bag]

842
00:32:21,627 --> 00:32:25,436
[Carefully packing the leftover water too]

843
00:32:25,436 --> 00:32:28,225
[And the leftover cola from yesterday]

844
00:32:28,225 --> 00:32:30,772
[Slip right into the paper bag]

845
00:32:30,772 --> 00:32:34,806
[Packing the perfectly boiled eggs too]

846
00:32:34,806 --> 00:32:36,979
[And those go right in too]

847
00:32:36,979 --> 00:32:39,846
[Inside the paper bag: pajamas, water, cola,
eggs, spam, ramyeon, etc... lots of stuff]

848
00:32:39,846 --> 00:32:41,740
- Let's go, we gotta leave now.
- Yeah.

849
00:32:41,740 --> 00:32:44,103
[The trio heads out]

850
00:32:45,564 --> 00:32:48,821
[Attending to Yumi]
Thank you!

851
00:32:48,821 --> 00:32:51,616
- We didn't forget anything, right?
- Yep.

852
00:32:51,616 --> 00:32:53,843
Woo Shik, turn off the lights inside...

853
00:32:53,843 --> 00:32:56,105
[Woo Shik carefully turns off all the lights]

854
00:32:56,105 --> 00:32:57,301
Okay.

855
00:32:57,301 --> 00:32:59,461
[Lastly, making sure the door is locked tight]

856
00:32:59,461 --> 00:33:00,826
It's done.

857
00:33:00,826 --> 00:33:03,574
Let's get a quick picture.

858
00:33:03,574 --> 00:33:06,972
[Getting ready for a proof shot]

859
00:33:06,972 --> 00:33:08,627
One, two, three!

860
00:33:08,627 --> 00:33:10,631
- We had a great stay here!
- We had a great stay here!

861
00:33:10,631 --> 00:33:12,392
Thank you!

862
00:33:14,592 --> 00:33:16,532
Okay.

863
00:33:17,335 --> 00:33:18,515
- Wow!
- Let's go!

864
00:33:18,515 --> 00:33:20,182
[Heading to the car return location]

865
00:33:20,182 --> 00:33:21,994
A car-share vehicle.

866
00:33:21,994 --> 00:33:23,762
Open the door.

867
00:33:25,086 --> 00:33:29,313
[Piling the luggage and clothes into the trunk]

868
00:33:29,313 --> 00:33:31,368
Okay, I'll just set the navigation,
and we'll go.

869
00:33:31,368 --> 00:33:33,345
- I'm getting in.
- Yeah.

870
00:33:33,345 --> 00:33:34,387
[Woo Shik will close the gate and hop in]

871
00:33:34,387 --> 00:33:36,574
What is Choi Woo Shik doing?

872
00:33:36,574 --> 00:33:38,917
This place feels like my home.

873
00:33:38,917 --> 00:33:41,099
I'll just see you off here.

874
00:33:42,819 --> 00:33:44,981
Come visit often.

875
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:46,187
Wait a second!

876
00:33:46,187 --> 00:33:47,395
[Roleplay instantly shut down]

877
00:33:47,395 --> 00:33:49,629
Let's just leave without picking him up.

878
00:33:49,629 --> 00:33:51,975
[Just imagining it is hilarious]

879
00:33:51,975 --> 00:33:53,009
Come visit often!

880
00:33:53,009 --> 00:33:54,042
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

881
00:33:54,042 --> 00:33:56,494
[This time, they play along]
- Take care! - Take care!

882
00:33:56,494 --> 00:33:59,646
- Let's just go that far.
- Yeah, I was thinking the same thing.

883
00:33:59,646 --> 00:34:02,428
[While he locks the door, unaware of anything]

884
00:34:02,428 --> 00:34:04,082
- Woo Shik, take care!
- Yeah.

885
00:34:04,082 --> 00:34:05,460
- We're off!
- Yeah.

886
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:06,615
Yeah.

887
00:34:06,615 --> 00:34:08,375
[They suddenly drive off]
Go farther, keep going.

888
00:34:08,375 --> 00:34:09,988
[Seo Jun?]

889
00:34:09,988 --> 00:34:12,511
[Woo Shik, we're leaving first]

890
00:34:13,612 --> 00:34:16,188
Oh, they're going pretty far...

891
00:34:16,188 --> 00:34:18,554
[Driving off after checking the distance]

892
00:34:18,554 --> 00:34:21,247
[Teasing the youngest never fails]

893
00:34:21,247 --> 00:34:23,394
Ah, he's running over, hold on.

894
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:26,683
[Thankfully, he makes it in from just nearby]

895
00:34:27,825 --> 00:34:29,498
[Trying to play it cool]
Oh, dear.

896
00:34:29,498 --> 00:34:32,024
- Okay, let's go.
- Okay.

897
00:34:32,024 --> 00:34:34,332
We had a great time!

898
00:34:36,166 --> 00:34:41,339
[Leaving the peaceful village and
heading back to downtown Namwon]

899
00:34:41,339 --> 00:34:43,068
Did you guys sleep well?

900
00:34:43,068 --> 00:34:44,830
Well, better than yesterday.

901
00:34:44,830 --> 00:34:46,548
I slept even worse today.

902
00:34:46,548 --> 00:34:48,190
- Why?
- I kept waking up.

903
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:50,713
Did you know I woke you up
because I had a nightmare?

904
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:52,216
- What did you say? What dream?
- You don't remember?

905
00:34:52,216 --> 00:34:53,796
- After having a nightmare?
- Oh, you had a nightmare?

906
00:34:53,796 --> 00:34:55,234
- Yeah.
- What did you say?

907
00:34:55,234 --> 00:34:58,440
I got startled and went, "Ughhh," you know?
And then Seo Jun...

908
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:00,015
[A vivid reenactment]
I went, "Ughhh," and then...

909
00:35:00,015 --> 00:35:01,932
- Ah, really?
- For real.

910
00:35:01,932 --> 00:35:04,736
[This is a 100% real situation]

911
00:35:04,736 --> 00:35:06,778
Ughhh.

912
00:35:06,778 --> 00:35:08,853
- Why?
- Why?

913
00:35:08,853 --> 00:35:10,756
- No...
- Yeah.

914
00:35:10,756 --> 00:35:14,701
[He woke from the nightmare
with a mysterious conversation...]

915
00:35:14,701 --> 00:35:18,814
Ah, when I woke up screaming,
it was seriously so...

916
00:35:18,814 --> 00:35:21,083
[Just adorable]
It was so funny.

917
00:35:21,083 --> 00:35:24,241
Anyway, if we get the car, no questions asked,
we're going straight to Yeongdeok, okay?

918
00:35:24,241 --> 00:35:25,280
Yeah.

919
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,119
And if we don't get the car, Boseong?

920
00:35:27,119 --> 00:35:29,767
Yeah, because we'd have to take the train.

921
00:35:29,767 --> 00:35:31,970
The one to Boseong was at ten-something...

922
00:35:31,970 --> 00:35:35,350
- Was it 10:30?
- I think it was either 10:37 or 10:47.

923
00:35:35,350 --> 00:35:37,203
[9:13 AM, about an hour and a half left]

924
00:35:37,203 --> 00:35:38,975
Ah, I hope we get the car today.

925
00:35:38,975 --> 00:35:40,754
- Ah, seriously...
- Right.

926
00:35:40,754 --> 00:35:42,734
That would be the perfect style.

927
00:35:42,734 --> 00:35:45,638
- The problem is if we get phones.
- Exactly.

928
00:35:45,638 --> 00:35:47,353
Honestly, I don't even need my phone anymore.

929
00:35:47,353 --> 00:35:49,690
- But Woo Shik, don't you feel that too?
- What?

930
00:35:49,690 --> 00:35:51,216
If you don't have it,

931
00:35:51,216 --> 00:35:53,099
- you just stop watching Shorts, right?
- Yeah.

932
00:35:53,099 --> 00:35:55,147
- You only watch because it's there.
- I just watch because it's there.

933
00:35:55,147 --> 00:35:56,625
- It's just a habit.
- Right.

934
00:35:56,625 --> 00:35:58,405
Ah, I get so nervous doing that.

935
00:35:58,405 --> 00:36:00,438
- The draw?
- Yeah.

936
00:36:00,438 --> 00:36:01,811
Yumi, you should do the draw today.

937
00:36:01,811 --> 00:36:03,891
No, I don't think I can do it.

938
00:36:03,891 --> 00:36:06,251
- Yumi, you should do the draw today.
- Yeah, you should draw it.

939
00:36:06,251 --> 00:36:08,644
[Today, Yumi will do the draw]
- Ah... - Just leave it to fate.

940
00:36:08,644 --> 00:36:11,197
Wow, I almost wore dress shoes
for the opening...

941
00:36:11,197 --> 00:36:13,612
Oh, that would've been the worst.

942
00:36:13,612 --> 00:36:15,839
That coat looked really heavy though.

943
00:36:15,839 --> 00:36:17,739
It's really long and heavy.

944
00:36:17,739 --> 00:36:19,645
My shoulders keep drooping lower.

945
00:36:19,645 --> 00:36:21,457
Just give your coat to the producer.

946
00:36:21,457 --> 00:36:23,346
Yeah, I should make him wear it.

947
00:36:23,346 --> 00:36:24,937
[Looks around]

948
00:36:24,937 --> 00:36:26,699
According to the navigation, it's here.

949
00:36:26,699 --> 00:36:29,094
This is it. Wow!

950
00:36:29,094 --> 00:36:31,186
[Turning the corner,
the car-sharing zone appears]

951
00:36:31,186 --> 00:36:32,794
I should park properly.

952
00:36:32,794 --> 00:36:35,240
[Arrival complete]
Let's just get out first, and...

953
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:36,847
Good morning!

954
00:36:36,847 --> 00:36:38,411
Good morning!

955
00:36:38,411 --> 00:36:40,262
Why does your hair look so pretty now?

956
00:36:40,262 --> 00:36:42,071
Me? Actually...

957
00:36:42,071 --> 00:36:43,663
I actually had a perm before.

958
00:36:43,663 --> 00:36:45,607
Yeah, the hair dryer dried it really quickly.

959
00:36:45,607 --> 00:36:49,027
- Yumi, when did you go to the salon?
- Oh, well...

960
00:36:50,335 --> 00:36:52,657
- Okay, that's enough? Yeah.
- Yep.

961
00:36:52,657 --> 00:36:54,560
Ah, there's way too much luggage.

962
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:57,530
[More luggage every day... and the coat too]
This is really heavy too.

963
00:36:57,530 --> 00:37:00,646
I tried the outfit on last night,
and it was seriously so heavy.

964
00:37:00,646 --> 00:37:03,345
[So, about that...]

965
00:37:03,345 --> 00:37:04,418
Why, Woo Shik?

966
00:37:04,418 --> 00:37:06,499
So, Producer, maybe this and...

967
00:37:06,499 --> 00:37:07,725
[Immediately catches on]

968
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:09,282
Would you maybe like to trade with that?

969
00:37:09,282 --> 00:37:11,922
Because I think this would look
really good on you.

970
00:37:11,922 --> 00:37:13,506
- Oh, the clothes?
- Yeah.

971
00:37:13,506 --> 00:37:17,344
- You've got great fashion sense, Producer Na.
- You're right.

972
00:37:17,344 --> 00:37:20,840
[Now, fully committing to the sales pitch]
And this matches his personal color too, right?

973
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:22,702
- This is double-layered.
- It's double-layered, two layers.

974
00:37:22,702 --> 00:37:24,676
[Just try it on once]
Try this on first.

975
00:37:24,676 --> 00:37:27,270
- Oh!
- Oh!

976
00:37:27,270 --> 00:37:29,376
- It looks good on you though?
- Yeah, it actually looks good on you.

977
00:37:29,376 --> 00:37:31,508
It seriously suits you though.

978
00:37:31,508 --> 00:37:33,759
[Meanwhile, Woo Shik quickly changes into it]
- Hey, but... - Ah, good trade.

979
00:37:33,759 --> 00:37:35,437
- Thanks!
- This is...

980
00:37:35,437 --> 00:37:36,551
- You're trading?
- Ah, yes.

981
00:37:36,551 --> 00:37:37,728
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

982
00:37:37,728 --> 00:37:40,121
[Thankfully, he genuinely likes it...]
Good trade!

983
00:37:40,121 --> 00:37:42,694
Ah, now it finally feels like I'm traveling.

984
00:37:42,694 --> 00:37:44,191
Now we kind of match, right?

985
00:37:44,191 --> 00:37:47,401
- You look way lighter now.
- No, I mean now we actually match.

986
00:37:47,401 --> 00:37:48,960
The phone benefit from yesterday...

987
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,747
- Yeah.
- has now passed the 24-hour mark.

988
00:37:50,747 --> 00:37:51,910
- Oh...
- Yeah.

989
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:54,446
- So you can return the phones to me now.
- Alright!

990
00:37:54,446 --> 00:37:56,188
Turn it off, we don't need it.

991
00:37:56,188 --> 00:37:57,506
Yeah, we don't need this.

992
00:37:57,506 --> 00:37:59,837
It was just heavy... yeah.

993
00:37:59,837 --> 00:38:03,316
For day three, we'll give you
100,000 won each, 300,000 won total.

994
00:38:03,316 --> 00:38:05,522
- Oh, thank you!
- Thank you!

995
00:38:06,259 --> 00:38:07,841
[Expense report, Day 3 allowance +300,000 won,
remaining balance: 339,710 won]

996
00:38:07,841 --> 00:38:10,669
Following yesterday,
we'll do another benefit draw today.

997
00:38:10,669 --> 00:38:12,390
First, phones.

998
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:13,631
Second, lodging.

999
00:38:13,631 --> 00:38:15,110
And third, a vehicle.

1000
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:17,496
You'll draw one out of these three.

1001
00:38:17,496 --> 00:38:19,194
- Today...
- Today, this person...

1002
00:38:19,194 --> 00:38:21,258
[Today's benefit draw main character]
- Yumi. - Ms. Yumi.

1003
00:38:21,258 --> 00:38:23,227
Do each of you have something you want most?

1004
00:38:23,227 --> 00:38:24,504
Of course.

1005
00:38:24,504 --> 00:38:27,693
- But I can't say it right now.
- What is it?

1006
00:38:27,693 --> 00:38:30,045
- Should I say it?
- Yeah.

1007
00:38:30,045 --> 00:38:31,184
The car.

1008
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:32,238
- The car?
- Yeah.

1009
00:38:32,238 --> 00:38:33,231
Nice.

1010
00:38:33,231 --> 00:38:35,117
But I'm worried it won't come out if I say it.

1011
00:38:35,117 --> 00:38:36,472
[Just in case it jinxes it...]

1012
00:38:36,472 --> 00:38:37,469
Nice.

1013
00:38:37,469 --> 00:38:38,801
What about the others then?

1014
00:38:38,801 --> 00:38:43,808
We're spending way too much money
on transportation,

1015
00:38:43,808 --> 00:38:45,898
so a car would probably be best.

1016
00:38:45,898 --> 00:38:48,096
If we get the car benefit...

1017
00:38:48,096 --> 00:38:50,403
If we get to visit new places,

1018
00:38:50,403 --> 00:38:52,275
I thought that would be really nice.

1019
00:38:52,275 --> 00:38:54,326
[All three want the vehicle]

1020
00:38:54,326 --> 00:38:56,255
But if the phone comes out,

1021
00:38:56,255 --> 00:38:58,518
we can't really save money with it.

1022
00:38:58,518 --> 00:38:59,577
Are phones the worst option?

1023
00:38:59,577 --> 00:39:00,910
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1024
00:39:00,910 --> 00:39:02,897
Ah, but if I draw it...

1025
00:39:02,897 --> 00:39:04,022
Should I draw?

1026
00:39:04,022 --> 00:39:06,082
- Yeah, draw it.
- Of course, we trust you.

1027
00:39:06,082 --> 00:39:07,156
Let's do rock-paper-scissors.

1028
00:39:07,156 --> 00:39:08,830
- Come on.
- Come on.

1029
00:39:08,830 --> 00:39:11,410
Seo Jun, can I borrow your hat for a second?
I'll just put this in there briefly.

1030
00:39:11,410 --> 00:39:13,028
- Oh, in here?
- In here?

1031
00:39:13,028 --> 00:39:14,857
[To make it even fairer...]
Oh, you're using this?

1032
00:39:14,857 --> 00:39:16,992
We don't really have anything else.
Mix them well...

1033
00:39:16,992 --> 00:39:18,070
Here I go.

1034
00:39:18,070 --> 00:39:19,333
- Oh, right away?
- Right away?

1035
00:39:19,333 --> 00:39:20,818
[She picked immediately!]

1036
00:39:21,559 --> 00:39:24,850
[Po-po picks without hesitation]

1037
00:39:24,850 --> 00:39:26,886
How much time can I have for this?

1038
00:39:26,886 --> 00:39:29,576
- Time? We don't have much time.
- No, I mean...

1039
00:39:29,576 --> 00:39:33,184
[Okay, checking it right away]

1040
00:39:33,833 --> 00:39:35,488
- Oh, I think it's three syllables.
- No...

1041
00:39:35,488 --> 00:39:37,291
[Her expression starts to twist?]
Oh?

1042
00:39:39,294 --> 00:39:42,172
- No? It's not?
- What? What is it?

1043
00:39:43,305 --> 00:39:45,764
- Why?
- What?

1044
00:39:45,764 --> 00:39:47,506
Are you acting?

1045
00:39:48,146 --> 00:39:49,771
- I'm sorry...
- What? Why?

1046
00:39:49,771 --> 00:39:51,844
[What on earth is it?]
- What is it? - It's okay.

1047
00:39:51,844 --> 00:39:53,562
- Should I open it?
- Yeah.

1048
00:39:53,562 --> 00:39:56,314
[What benefit is hidden inside the paper?]

1049
00:39:56,314 --> 00:39:58,433
[Phones two times in a row]

1050
00:39:58,433 --> 00:40:00,692
[By Jung Yumi]

1051
00:40:04,783 --> 00:40:06,658
No way...

1052
00:40:06,658 --> 00:40:08,480
- No way!
- This is the worst-case scenario...

1053
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:10,425
- we talked about yesterday.
- What is this?

1054
00:40:10,425 --> 00:40:11,978
[No, this can't be it...]

1055
00:40:11,978 --> 00:40:15,115
I told you this wouldn't work, right?
I shouldn't say it out loud.

1056
00:40:15,115 --> 00:40:18,196
Honestly, this morning I was only hoping
the phone wouldn't come out.

1057
00:40:18,196 --> 00:40:20,116
But I ended up drawing it with my own hand.

1058
00:40:20,116 --> 00:40:22,566
Just thinking about it made me hate it.

1059
00:40:22,566 --> 00:40:26,619
It made us realize what it's like
traveling without phones.

1060
00:40:26,619 --> 00:40:29,852
Traveling without phones is actually more fun,

1061
00:40:29,852 --> 00:40:32,075
so we don't really feel the need to use them.

1062
00:40:32,075 --> 00:40:34,866
[But phones are benefits too...]

1063
00:40:34,866 --> 00:40:36,973
Oh, wait a second.

1064
00:40:36,973 --> 00:40:39,058
I'll give you back the same ones.

1065
00:40:39,058 --> 00:40:41,538
[Please take the phones back again]
Oh! This...

1066
00:40:41,538 --> 00:40:42,688
How did this...

1067
00:40:42,688 --> 00:40:44,862
I tell it not to come back, but it still does.

1068
00:40:44,862 --> 00:40:46,939
Oh, I seriously don't need a phone though.

1069
00:40:46,939 --> 00:40:49,488
- Oh, wait, then what should we do?
- What should we do?

1070
00:40:49,488 --> 00:40:50,825
Ah, this is bad.

1071
00:40:50,825 --> 00:40:53,481
- Should we sell this?
- Anyone want to buy this?

1072
00:40:53,481 --> 00:40:54,955
[The troubled age of smartphones]

1073
00:40:54,955 --> 00:40:58,331
Then for now, we're going to Boseong then?

1074
00:40:58,331 --> 00:40:59,568
- Right.
- Right.

1075
00:40:59,568 --> 00:41:01,964
- Yeah, I'm okay with it, sounds good.
- Boseong sounds good.

1076
00:41:01,964 --> 00:41:05,048
- We should leave now.
- Yeah, we need to go to Namwon Station.

1077
00:41:05,048 --> 00:41:06,823
Let's go!

1078
00:41:06,823 --> 00:41:09,133
Starting tomorrow, let's decide
with rock-paper-scissors who draws.

1079
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:10,392
- Tomorrow, I'll draw.
- Well, for now...

1080
00:41:10,392 --> 00:41:11,832
[Only Seo Jun hasn't drawn yet]

1081
00:41:11,832 --> 00:41:13,608
Ah, I hope the car comes out tomorrow.

1082
00:41:13,608 --> 00:41:15,717
- But I do want to visit Boseong too!
- Yeah, I want to go.

1083
00:41:15,717 --> 00:41:16,847
Yeah. I really want to go.

1084
00:41:16,847 --> 00:41:20,014
[After a 10-minute taxi ride]

1085
00:41:20,014 --> 00:41:23,675
[They plan to travel by train
for about an hour and a half]

1086
00:41:23,675 --> 00:41:25,010
You're okay with it, right?

1087
00:41:25,010 --> 00:41:26,869
- Of course.
- Of course.

1088
00:41:26,869 --> 00:41:29,079
- Honestly, I wanted to go to Boseong.
- I want to go to Boseong too.

1089
00:41:29,079 --> 00:41:32,360
But earlier, I seriously
didn't want to say "the car."

1090
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:34,605
But I felt like I had to
say something, so I did.

1091
00:41:34,605 --> 00:41:35,897
You did fine.

1092
00:41:35,897 --> 00:41:39,612
They say you shouldn't say
your real wish out loud.

1093
00:41:39,612 --> 00:41:42,300
Tomorrow, I should keep quiet and do it.

1094
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:44,889
- The taxi is on the other side though.
- Oh?

1095
00:41:44,889 --> 00:41:46,093
Taxi available?

1096
00:41:46,093 --> 00:41:49,247
[They quickly flag down a passing taxi]

1097
00:41:49,247 --> 00:41:51,236
Namwon Station, please.

1098
00:41:51,236 --> 00:41:54,075
- The station area?
- Yes, Namwon Station.

1099
00:41:54,075 --> 00:41:56,373
Ah, now it finally feels like traveling.

1100
00:41:56,373 --> 00:41:57,550
[The first day it really feels like a trip]

1101
00:41:57,550 --> 00:42:01,036
- I was the only one in the opening scene.
- You just appeared like a goblin alone...

1102
00:42:02,523 --> 00:42:06,558
Later on the train, we should look up
a guesthouse in Boseong.

1103
00:42:06,558 --> 00:42:08,100
- Yeah, we should.
- We should.

1104
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:11,446
- They are convenient for things like that.
- Yeah.

1105
00:42:11,446 --> 00:42:14,046
Seriously though, I didn't expect phones again.

1106
00:42:14,046 --> 00:42:18,237
I never hesitate with things like draws.

1107
00:42:18,237 --> 00:42:20,268
But next time, take your time before you draw.

1108
00:42:20,268 --> 00:42:22,281
[Clenching lips tight...]

1109
00:42:22,281 --> 00:42:24,684
Now that we're going to Boseong,
if we get the car,

1110
00:42:24,684 --> 00:42:28,194
should we rethink our destination a bit?

1111
00:42:28,194 --> 00:42:31,314
But I keep feeling like the car
isn't going to come out.

1112
00:42:31,314 --> 00:42:32,509
[An ominous feeling lingers into tomorrow...]

1113
00:42:32,509 --> 00:42:33,766
Till the end.

1114
00:42:33,766 --> 00:42:35,610
[The following morning]
Oh, please...

1115
00:42:35,610 --> 00:42:37,762
[The long-awaited third benefit draw]
Please... Seo Jun, you've got good luck.

1116
00:42:37,762 --> 00:42:39,190
I'm nervous right now.

1117
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:40,337
[Will they finally get a car
from the draw tomorrow?]

1118
00:42:40,337 --> 00:42:43,429
- Please...
- Oh, please!

1119
00:42:44,197 --> 00:42:46,697
Was Namwon Station always this far?

1120
00:42:46,697 --> 00:42:47,970
Oh, it's right there.

1121
00:42:47,970 --> 00:42:49,010
[Almost at Namwon Station]

1122
00:42:49,010 --> 00:42:51,130
If we'd taken the bus, we would've been late.

1123
00:42:51,130 --> 00:42:53,456
Since we spent a bit on transportation today...

1124
00:42:53,456 --> 00:42:56,309
- Yeah.
- Let's keep lunch really cheap.

1125
00:42:56,309 --> 00:42:58,275
- At least for dinner later?
- Yeah.

1126
00:42:58,275 --> 00:43:00,716
A raw fish place near the beach would be nice.

1127
00:43:00,716 --> 00:43:03,034
- Raw fish in Boseong?
- Yeah.

1128
00:43:03,034 --> 00:43:04,923
We're almost there.

1129
00:43:06,266 --> 00:43:08,775
[They reached Namwon Station just by
crossing the road, no mountains involved]

1130
00:43:08,775 --> 00:43:10,755
- Yep, thank you!
- Thank you.

1131
00:43:10,755 --> 00:43:12,243
Thank you!

1132
00:43:12,243 --> 00:43:13,982
<i>The payment amount is 6,300 won.</i>

1133
00:43:13,982 --> 00:43:16,448
6,300 won.

1134
00:43:16,448 --> 00:43:18,375
We'll pay 6,300 won.

1135
00:43:18,375 --> 00:43:20,295
[Expense report, taxi fare, -6,300 won]
Yes, thank you!

1136
00:43:20,295 --> 00:43:23,168
- Thank you, have a nice day!
- Thank you.

1137
00:43:26,088 --> 00:43:27,135
[First, they go buy train tickets]

1138
00:43:27,135 --> 00:43:29,148
- Hello!
- Hello!

1139
00:43:29,148 --> 00:43:30,867
- Where are you headed?
- Boseong.

1140
00:43:30,867 --> 00:43:32,125
- Pardon?
- Boseong!

1141
00:43:32,125 --> 00:43:34,732
To get to Boseong, you'll have to
transfer at Suncheon, right?

1142
00:43:34,732 --> 00:43:35,738
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

1143
00:43:35,738 --> 00:43:36,892
Please proceed with the payment.

1144
00:43:36,892 --> 00:43:37,993
How much is it?

1145
00:43:37,993 --> 00:43:40,451
It's 27,900 won.

1146
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:41,878
To go all the way to Boseong?

1147
00:43:41,878 --> 00:43:43,291
- Yes.
- Oh!

1148
00:43:43,291 --> 00:43:45,031
- For three people?
- Three people.

1149
00:43:45,031 --> 00:43:46,358
- Yes.
- Oh...

1150
00:43:46,358 --> 00:43:47,896
[Expense report, 3 train tickets, -27,900 won]
Wow, that seems pretty good.

1151
00:43:47,896 --> 00:43:49,169
Yeah, it's really good.

1152
00:43:49,169 --> 00:43:51,149
- Thank you.
- Yeah!

1153
00:43:51,796 --> 00:43:53,148
[They immediately take another proof shot]

1154
00:43:53,148 --> 00:43:56,645
[Total travel time, 1 hr 44 min]
Today, the KTX to Suncheon departs at 10:47.

1155
00:43:56,645 --> 00:44:00,777
From Suncheon to Boseong,
you'll take the Mugunghwa train at 11:33.

1156
00:44:00,777 --> 00:44:02,486
Maybe we should get something to eat.

1157
00:44:02,486 --> 00:44:04,042
[10:32 AM / About 15 minutes left]
Should we go in?

1158
00:44:04,042 --> 00:44:05,791
Want some coffee?

1159
00:44:05,791 --> 00:44:07,756
Coffee sounds good.
Oh, they sell sandwiches here.

1160
00:44:07,756 --> 00:44:09,142
How much is it?

1161
00:44:09,142 --> 00:44:10,236
[Whoosh]

1162
00:44:10,236 --> 00:44:12,031
Let's check how much it is over there.

1163
00:44:12,031 --> 00:44:13,711
We need to save as much as possible for dinner.

1164
00:44:13,711 --> 00:44:16,591
- Yeah.
- So we can eat something delicious.

1165
00:44:16,591 --> 00:44:18,657
[Entering another convenience store]
Oh, they have stuff here too?

1166
00:44:18,657 --> 00:44:21,546
They've got triangle gimbap here.

1167
00:44:21,546 --> 00:44:23,475
- Get a sandwich if you're gonna eat.
- Yeah.

1168
00:44:23,475 --> 00:44:24,661
What about you, Seo Jun?

1169
00:44:24,661 --> 00:44:26,247
I'll have this.

1170
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:27,322
Yumi, have some too.

1171
00:44:27,322 --> 00:44:30,362
- I'll get tuna mayo triangle gimbap.
- Okay.

1172
00:44:30,362 --> 00:44:33,170
- We might get thirsty.
- We brought water.

1173
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:34,418
[Always carrying everything just in case]
Okay.

1174
00:44:34,418 --> 00:44:36,787
- A mint candy?
- Yeah, should we get one?

1175
00:44:36,787 --> 00:44:39,131
[They even buy mint candy]
- What do you think? - Okay!

1176
00:44:39,131 --> 00:44:40,644
Yes, that'll be 9,300 won.

1177
00:44:40,644 --> 00:44:42,405
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1178
00:44:42,405 --> 00:44:44,307
[Expense report, lunch, -9,300 won]
- Thank you. - Thank you!

1179
00:44:44,307 --> 00:44:48,719
- Can we eat this outside?
- Yes, you can eat inside here as well.

1180
00:44:48,719 --> 00:44:50,586
Ten minutes left.

1181
00:44:51,699 --> 00:44:54,419
[Director Choi's food insert shots continue]

1182
00:44:54,419 --> 00:44:56,565
[Woo Shik's sandwich]

1183
00:44:56,565 --> 00:44:58,421
[Seo Jun's bulgogi burger]

1184
00:44:58,421 --> 00:45:00,579
[Yumi's triangle gimbap]

1185
00:45:00,579 --> 00:45:04,119
[Still, it's a pretty filling lunch
with one menu each]

1186
00:45:04,119 --> 00:45:05,952
- This is good.
- Is it good?

1187
00:45:05,952 --> 00:45:07,318
Let's see inside.

1188
00:45:07,318 --> 00:45:08,611
[The burger's got a pretty solid setup]

1189
00:45:08,611 --> 00:45:10,405
Ah, I should've gotten this too.

1190
00:45:10,405 --> 00:45:11,532
[Wanna take a bite?]

1191
00:45:11,532 --> 00:45:12,684
- Can I eat it?
- Yeah.

1192
00:45:12,684 --> 00:45:13,837
[Take a big bite]

1193
00:45:13,837 --> 00:45:15,338
I think that was the tastiest part just now?

1194
00:45:15,338 --> 00:45:18,287
I gave you my favorite middle part, okay?

1195
00:45:20,658 --> 00:45:23,086
[Wanna take a bite?]

1196
00:45:23,086 --> 00:45:25,103
[The edge of the bread]
No, I don't want it.

1197
00:45:25,103 --> 00:45:26,834
But that's Woo Shik's absolute favorite part.

1198
00:45:26,834 --> 00:45:28,533
- It's my favorite part.
- No thanks.

1199
00:45:28,533 --> 00:45:30,747
It tastes better warmed up.

1200
00:45:30,747 --> 00:45:32,273
[Retry]

1201
00:45:32,273 --> 00:45:33,991
[Rejected]

1202
00:45:33,991 --> 00:45:36,549
Can you pass me the water?
It's getting stuck in my throat.

1203
00:45:36,549 --> 00:45:38,435
Want some water?

1204
00:45:38,435 --> 00:45:41,399
- Or cola?
- Huh? Oh...

1205
00:45:41,399 --> 00:45:43,833
Seo Jun, sorry, but...

1206
00:45:43,833 --> 00:45:46,771
- Could you pay the extra 1,400 won?
- Ah, okay.

1207
00:45:46,771 --> 00:45:49,019
Wow, you really don't cut anyone any slack.

1208
00:45:49,019 --> 00:45:50,702
[The "extra fee" here refers to...]

1209
00:45:50,702 --> 00:45:52,042
You have to press "return."

1210
00:45:52,042 --> 00:45:54,272
[While returning the car-sharing vehicle...]
Please lock the car doors.

1211
00:45:54,272 --> 00:45:55,665
1,470 won.

1212
00:45:55,665 --> 00:45:58,117
[Distance-based fee added]

1213
00:45:58,117 --> 00:45:59,598
Then I'll collect 1,470 won later.

1214
00:45:59,598 --> 00:46:00,658
- Alright.
- Okay.

1215
00:46:00,658 --> 00:46:02,538
Got it.

1216
00:46:02,538 --> 00:46:05,458
I don't have 70 won in change,
so I'll just give it to you.

1217
00:46:05,458 --> 00:46:08,684
Thank you!

1218
00:46:10,020 --> 00:46:13,231
I don't have change either,
so I'll just give you 1,500 won.

1219
00:46:13,231 --> 00:46:14,877
- Wow!
- Yeah.

1220
00:46:14,877 --> 00:46:17,888
[Expense report, extra fee, -1,500 won,
remaining balance: 294,710 won]

1221
00:46:17,888 --> 00:46:19,471
Oh, preparing for boarding?

1222
00:46:19,471 --> 00:46:21,743
- Did it arrive?
- Yeah, I guess so.

1223
00:46:21,743 --> 00:46:25,097
[Five minutes before arrival]

1224
00:46:25,097 --> 00:46:28,807
Train No. 5, bound for Yeosu Expo.

1225
00:46:28,807 --> 00:46:30,496
I think ours is platform 2?

1226
00:46:30,496 --> 00:46:32,966
- Platform 2.
- Yeah, Yeosu.

1227
00:46:32,966 --> 00:46:34,250
Hasn't it arrived yet?

1228
00:46:34,250 --> 00:46:35,699
Not yet.

1229
00:46:36,389 --> 00:46:40,104
[Yumi's scarf fell... no, her clothes...]

1230
00:46:40,104 --> 00:46:42,493
[No one noticed]

1231
00:46:42,493 --> 00:46:45,043
"Train to Busan!"
The stars of "Train to Busan."

1232
00:46:45,043 --> 00:46:47,313
[Four minutes before arrival]

1233
00:46:47,313 --> 00:46:49,232
Let me imitate Yumi a bit.

1234
00:46:49,232 --> 00:46:52,093
Oh, no... stop it! Get up!

1235
00:46:52,093 --> 00:46:54,406
[Guess who Yumi is?]

1236
00:46:54,406 --> 00:46:56,906
[Three minutes before arrival]
And she was in that position for quite a while.

1237
00:46:56,906 --> 00:46:59,037
[Now they finally start gathering their stuff]
You just left the phone like this?

1238
00:46:59,037 --> 00:47:01,344
Well, there are people around... Where'd it go?

1239
00:47:01,344 --> 00:47:03,137
Maybe it fell, did you see it?

1240
00:47:03,137 --> 00:47:04,453
Not the scarf, but...

1241
00:47:04,453 --> 00:47:05,948
It's clothing.

1242
00:47:05,948 --> 00:47:07,872
It might've fallen... did you see it?

1243
00:47:07,872 --> 00:47:09,165
I didn't see it.

1244
00:47:09,165 --> 00:47:10,531
- It's probably in the bag.
- Yeah, probably.

1245
00:47:10,531 --> 00:47:11,818
It's probably in the bag.

1246
00:47:11,818 --> 00:47:14,697
Knowing her personality,
there's no way she forgot it.

1247
00:47:14,697 --> 00:47:17,660
- Yeah, it'll be at the bottom.
- I trust you.

1248
00:47:20,119 --> 00:47:21,598
You must've left it upstairs.

1249
00:47:21,598 --> 00:47:23,412
Oh, wait a second.

1250
00:47:23,412 --> 00:47:24,932
- Go quickly and come back.
- Okay.

1251
00:47:24,932 --> 00:47:28,112
- Hurry.
- Why didn't you tell me that?

1252
00:47:28,112 --> 00:47:31,132
[The scarf rescue team sets off]

1253
00:47:32,222 --> 00:47:33,671
Really?

1254
00:47:38,983 --> 00:47:41,551
[It's the scarf?]
- Did you drop it on purpose? - No...

1255
00:47:41,551 --> 00:47:43,257
[Just ten seconds earlier]

1256
00:47:43,257 --> 00:47:46,589
[Look carefully to the right]

1257
00:47:46,589 --> 00:47:49,482
[Someone brought the scarf just in time!]

1258
00:47:49,482 --> 00:47:52,104
- Ah, did you drop it on purpose?
- No, she dropped it just now.

1259
00:47:52,104 --> 00:47:54,619
Yumi! Yumi, it's here!

1260
00:47:54,619 --> 00:47:56,845
[An echo that never comes back...]
Thank you!

1261
00:47:56,845 --> 00:47:58,697
- The timing is...
- Thank you.

1262
00:47:58,697 --> 00:48:01,337
Like it was scripted...
it seriously feels scripted.

1263
00:48:01,337 --> 00:48:02,922
[Woo Shik is already wearing it]

1264
00:48:02,922 --> 00:48:06,994
[Meanwhile, Yumi goes up unaware]
Oh, no, what should I do?

1265
00:48:06,994 --> 00:48:08,473
Where is it?

1266
00:48:08,473 --> 00:48:10,551
Tell me where it is!

1267
00:48:10,551 --> 00:48:12,221
Seriously...

1268
00:48:14,391 --> 00:48:16,480
This is driving me crazy.

1269
00:48:17,780 --> 00:48:19,074
[She ended up all the way back
at the lunch spot]

1270
00:48:19,074 --> 00:48:22,120
Sorry.

1271
00:48:22,120 --> 00:48:24,746
[A phone call comes in
from the staff following her...]

1272
00:48:24,746 --> 00:48:26,939
- Where is it? It's not here though?
- Oh, really?

1273
00:48:26,939 --> 00:48:28,712
- I just got a call.
- Yeah.

1274
00:48:28,712 --> 00:48:31,139
- Someone picked it up and gave it to Woo Shik.
- Really?

1275
00:48:31,139 --> 00:48:33,238
[She finally learns the truth]

1276
00:48:33,238 --> 00:48:35,091
She's running back again.

1277
00:48:35,091 --> 00:48:38,458
[One minute before arrival]
I hope she doesn't fall like that.

1278
00:48:38,458 --> 00:48:40,912
Oh dear, I brought it over for you.

1279
00:48:40,912 --> 00:48:44,013
- Thank you.
- You left it right there.

1280
00:48:44,013 --> 00:48:45,398
- Really?
- Yeah.

1281
00:48:45,398 --> 00:48:47,485
Oh my, thank you!

1282
00:48:47,485 --> 00:48:49,404
Thank you!

1283
00:48:49,404 --> 00:48:51,937
But I brought this back instead!

1284
00:48:51,937 --> 00:48:53,944
Where did that come from?
Did you leave that behind?

1285
00:48:53,944 --> 00:48:55,337
- Yeah.
- Seriously...

1286
00:48:55,337 --> 00:48:56,403
I...

1287
00:48:56,403 --> 00:48:57,843
[Panting]

1288
00:48:57,843 --> 00:49:00,003
I'm gonna rewrite the drama again.

1289
00:49:00,003 --> 00:49:01,283
Hey!

1290
00:49:01,283 --> 00:49:03,229
I told you we had to save this!

1291
00:49:03,229 --> 00:49:05,858
I went all the way back because of this.

1292
00:49:05,858 --> 00:49:08,831
- Where'd you get that?
- You went back to get this?

1293
00:49:08,831 --> 00:49:09,864
Yeah!

1294
00:49:09,864 --> 00:49:12,257
- Ah, to get this...
- Yeah, because we...

1295
00:49:12,257 --> 00:49:13,415
- Eggs.
- Oh...

1296
00:49:13,415 --> 00:49:15,850
- Oh, Yumi...
- We still have to eat the eggs, you know.

1297
00:49:15,850 --> 00:49:19,749
- Yumi's seriously such a thoughtful person.
- Jeez.

1298
00:49:19,749 --> 00:49:22,360
- I suddenly noticed the cola was gone.
- Yeah, exactly.

1299
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:24,780
[One cola saved Po-po's reputation]
- This is only 1,000 won... - See?

1300
00:49:25,406 --> 00:49:26,972
Oh, it's coming!

1301
00:49:26,972 --> 00:49:29,846
[Train arriving]

1302
00:49:29,846 --> 00:49:35,293
[The train to Suncheon
arrives at the transfer station]

1303
00:49:36,866 --> 00:49:40,324
[The trio strides over to find their seats]

1304
00:49:40,324 --> 00:49:42,605
Wow, it's first class!

1305
00:49:42,605 --> 00:49:44,776
- This is Car 2 though?
- Really?

1306
00:49:44,776 --> 00:49:46,915
Let's move from here. Let's board first.

1307
00:49:46,915 --> 00:49:48,436
[They decide to board first and move to Car 1]

1308
00:49:48,436 --> 00:49:50,650
- We're seated 33.
- 33?

1309
00:49:50,650 --> 00:49:53,063
[10:47 AM / Train to Suncheon]

1310
00:49:53,063 --> 00:49:57,089
[Successfully boarded the first train]

1311
00:49:58,433 --> 00:50:01,165
[The first train ride will take 36 minutes]

1312
00:50:01,165 --> 00:50:04,065
[They each take a little personal time]

1313
00:50:04,065 --> 00:50:05,151
[Staring]

1314
00:50:05,151 --> 00:50:07,642
[Woo Shik staring off somewhere]

1315
00:50:07,642 --> 00:50:10,786
[Watching Shorts again]

1316
00:50:10,786 --> 00:50:13,139
[Quick dopamine fix]

1317
00:50:13,139 --> 00:50:15,279
Wow, that's cool!

1318
00:50:15,279 --> 00:50:17,172
- Where is that? Gwangju?
- No.

1319
00:50:17,172 --> 00:50:18,299
A green tea field.

1320
00:50:18,299 --> 00:50:20,552
It's a tea plantation,
and they also run a pension there.

1321
00:50:20,552 --> 00:50:22,566
[Po-po looks up places to stay in Boseong]

1322
00:50:22,566 --> 00:50:24,373
That's nice.

1323
00:50:24,373 --> 00:50:27,220
There are a lot of places like this.
Tea plantations.

1324
00:50:27,220 --> 00:50:28,893
Tea plantation?

1325
00:50:28,893 --> 00:50:30,449
We...

1326
00:50:30,449 --> 00:50:32,968
The first day, 60,000... 120,000 won.

1327
00:50:32,968 --> 00:50:35,914
[While Yumi calculates lodging costs]

1328
00:50:35,914 --> 00:50:39,089
[Before he knows it, Seo Jun falls asleep]

1329
00:50:39,089 --> 00:50:42,415
[Eventually, Yumi also falls asleep]

1330
00:50:42,415 --> 00:50:43,875
[Day 3 of the trip]

1331
00:50:43,875 --> 00:50:47,981
[As they recover from accumulated fatigue]

1332
00:50:47,981 --> 00:50:51,769
[Suncheon]
[They've arrived at the transfer station]

1333
00:50:51,769 --> 00:50:54,675
- This is Suncheon now, right?
- Yeah.

1334
00:50:54,675 --> 00:50:57,456
[The two wake up at perfect timing]

1335
00:50:57,456 --> 00:51:01,919
[And continue on feeling refreshed]

1336
00:51:01,919 --> 00:51:04,299
[11:26 AM / Suncheon Station]

1337
00:51:04,299 --> 00:51:07,552
- Where do we go to board the Mugunghwa train?
- Oh, go to Platform 2.

1338
00:51:07,552 --> 00:51:09,097
- Are you heading to Boseong?
- Yeah.

1339
00:51:09,097 --> 00:51:11,809
- I heard it was Platform 2.
- Ah, okay, thank you.

1340
00:51:11,809 --> 00:51:12,890
Thank you.

1341
00:51:12,890 --> 00:51:16,274
[They hurry to the transfer platform]

1342
00:51:16,274 --> 00:51:18,861
- Did she say Platform 2?
- Platform 2.

1343
00:51:18,861 --> 00:51:20,160
Here?

1344
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:22,501
[As long as they find the right platform]

1345
00:51:22,501 --> 00:51:26,560
[Easier-than-expected train transfer]

1346
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:28,758
The train's already here.

1347
00:51:28,758 --> 00:51:29,856
It's here?

1348
00:51:29,856 --> 00:51:31,011
- Oh, this one?
- Yeah.

1349
00:51:31,011 --> 00:51:32,377
It's got a vibe.

1350
00:51:32,377 --> 00:51:34,233
[The connecting train is
a charming Mugunghwa train]

1351
00:51:34,233 --> 00:51:38,042
[It's a tiny train with only two cars]

1352
00:51:38,042 --> 00:51:40,124
- It's seriously cute.
- Wow, it's tiny.

1353
00:51:40,124 --> 00:51:41,302
Here it is.

1354
00:51:41,302 --> 00:51:42,571
- That's the whole thing.
- Yeah.

1355
00:51:42,571 --> 00:51:44,644
[The Mugunghwa train still has
plenty of charm after all this time]

1356
00:51:45,397 --> 00:51:48,604
[Seo Jun is showing off his charm too]

1357
00:51:49,627 --> 00:51:52,567
Hurry! Zombie! Move!

1358
00:51:52,567 --> 00:51:55,174
[The trio boards with excitement]

1359
00:51:55,174 --> 00:51:57,188
Doesn't it feel roomier?

1360
00:51:57,188 --> 00:51:59,263
[Falling in love]

1361
00:51:59,263 --> 00:52:01,588
<i>The train will depart shortly.</i>

1362
00:52:03,394 --> 00:52:05,517
Feels like we're time-traveling.

1363
00:52:05,517 --> 00:52:11,499
[Heading to Boseong
while enjoying the nostalgic vibes]

1364
00:52:12,751 --> 00:52:16,175
[The second train ride will take 58 minutes]

1365
00:52:16,175 --> 00:52:17,664
Now we...

1366
00:52:17,664 --> 00:52:20,458
once we get off at Boseong Station,

1367
00:52:20,458 --> 00:52:23,138
we should talk about where to go.

1368
00:52:24,522 --> 00:52:26,712
- Is that in Boseong?
- Yeah.

1369
00:52:26,712 --> 00:52:29,192
Wow, Goryeo ***gwan looks delicious.

1370
00:52:30,318 --> 00:52:31,880
[Woo Shik even searches through Shorts]

1371
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:33,800
There are lots of cockles here?

1372
00:52:34,505 --> 00:52:36,979
It's Beolgyo, cockles are their thing.

1373
00:52:36,979 --> 00:52:40,493
[This is Beolgyo-eup, Boseong-gun]

1374
00:52:40,493 --> 00:52:42,617
Original Boseong green tea tteokgalbi.

1375
00:52:42,617 --> 00:52:44,515
Wow, looks tasty.

1376
00:52:45,143 --> 00:52:46,648
Live octopus...

1377
00:52:46,648 --> 00:52:48,268
Wow, look at those shrimp.

1378
00:52:48,268 --> 00:52:50,162
Wow, they're big!

1379
00:52:51,062 --> 00:52:54,078
Sliced raw gizzard shad must be delicious, wow.

1380
00:52:54,078 --> 00:52:56,581
- It's not the season for gizzard shad...
- Must be expensive though?

1381
00:52:56,581 --> 00:52:58,379
We should check out this forest too.

1382
00:52:58,379 --> 00:53:01,085
Dae*** Tea Plantation, we have to go here.

1383
00:53:01,792 --> 00:53:04,722
Looks like they sell green tea ice cream
and stuff like that.

1384
00:53:04,722 --> 00:53:06,085
Nice!

1385
00:53:06,085 --> 00:53:07,542
I want to go there.

1386
00:53:07,542 --> 00:53:09,207
[After picking where he wants to go]

1387
00:53:09,207 --> 00:53:12,942
[Seo Jun is the first to pass out]

1388
00:53:12,942 --> 00:53:14,533
[Sunglasses case]

1389
00:53:14,533 --> 00:53:16,748
[T-shirt]

1390
00:53:16,748 --> 00:53:22,103
[Yumi makes a neck pillow and falls asleep]

1391
00:53:24,373 --> 00:53:27,266
[Silence returns once again...]

1392
00:53:27,266 --> 00:53:31,229
[A strange sense of déjà vu...]

1393
00:53:31,229 --> 00:53:35,689
[Not only the trio...]

1394
00:53:37,219 --> 00:53:41,016
[This time even the staff has fallen asleep...]

1395
00:53:41,016 --> 00:53:45,216
<i>Our train will soon
arrive at Deukryang Station.</i>

1396
00:53:45,216 --> 00:53:47,249
[Q. You guys really only slept on the train?]
I kept sleeping and waking up.

1397
00:53:47,249 --> 00:53:50,378
I honestly wished it would go
just one more hour.

1398
00:53:50,378 --> 00:53:52,178
Weren't you all thinking the same thing?

1399
00:53:52,178 --> 00:53:54,864
The kind of train trip I imagine is...

1400
00:53:54,864 --> 00:54:00,209
I imagined eating eggs and drinking soda
with that kind of vibe.

1401
00:54:00,209 --> 00:54:02,496
But we all passed out as soon as we boarded,

1402
00:54:02,496 --> 00:54:05,609
so I barely remember the Mugunghwa train.

1403
00:54:05,609 --> 00:54:08,339
So when are we eating the eggs?

1404
00:54:08,339 --> 00:54:11,465
- Later.
- I forgot we even had eggs.

1405
00:54:11,465 --> 00:54:12,587
[Thinking deeply...]

1406
00:54:12,587 --> 00:54:15,259
We'll just eat them at the green tea fields.

1407
00:54:15,259 --> 00:54:18,087
My neck hurts so much from headbanging.

1408
00:54:18,910 --> 00:54:21,386
- It felt like this.
- Yeah.

1409
00:54:21,386 --> 00:54:23,250
More than the KTX...

1410
00:54:23,250 --> 00:54:25,389
Can we really take this?

1411
00:54:25,389 --> 00:54:26,681
[What is happening right now?]
Really?

1412
00:54:26,681 --> 00:54:28,619
Oh, thank you!

1413
00:54:29,770 --> 00:54:31,014
Can we really take this?

1414
00:54:31,014 --> 00:54:32,100
[Before exit, given a "Dubai chewy cookie"]

1415
00:54:32,100 --> 00:54:33,027
Really?

1416
00:54:33,027 --> 00:54:35,243
[Nods]
Thank you so much!

1417
00:54:35,243 --> 00:54:36,693
Dubai chewy cookie?

1418
00:54:36,693 --> 00:54:39,116
A human "Dubai chewy cookie" is right here.

1419
00:54:39,116 --> 00:54:41,319
Sorry, but could you pass it
over one more time...

1420
00:54:41,319 --> 00:54:44,108
[Director Choi missed the shot,
so they're filming it one more time]

1421
00:54:44,108 --> 00:54:46,935
Huh? Oh, what is this?

1422
00:54:48,634 --> 00:54:52,059
[Yumi and the passenger go all in]
Really? Wow, can you really give this to us?

1423
00:54:52,059 --> 00:54:54,035
Something this precious?

1424
00:54:54,035 --> 00:54:55,597
- Oh, really?
- Where are you headed?

1425
00:54:55,597 --> 00:54:56,711
To Hwasun.

1426
00:54:56,711 --> 00:54:59,016
- Hwasun! Why?
- Hwasun!

1427
00:54:59,016 --> 00:55:00,386
[Yes, that's right]
Hwasun, Jeollanam-do Province.

1428
00:55:00,386 --> 00:55:02,632
- Oh, are you traveling?
- I'm going to meet a friend.

1429
00:55:02,632 --> 00:55:04,098
[They naturally make some small talk]

1430
00:55:04,098 --> 00:55:06,697
- We have to get off.
- There's more, right?

1431
00:55:06,697 --> 00:55:09,206
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1432
00:55:09,206 --> 00:55:12,552
- We'll enjoy it.
- Have a nice trip!

1433
00:55:12,552 --> 00:55:17,453
[They arrive at Boseong Station]
<i>Our train will soon arrive at Boseong Station.</i>

1434
00:55:17,453 --> 00:55:19,706
[The third destination: Boseong]

1435
00:55:19,706 --> 00:55:21,946
[The capital of green tea,
covered in rolling green waves]

1436
00:55:21,946 --> 00:55:24,142
[At the southern tip of Korea]

1437
00:55:24,142 --> 00:55:26,733
[Where it meets the refreshing sea]

1438
00:55:26,733 --> 00:55:28,969
[This is Boseong]

1439
00:55:28,969 --> 00:55:30,409
[12:32 PM / Boseong Station]
Where should we go?

1440
00:55:30,409 --> 00:55:32,402
I think that's the crossing over there.

1441
00:55:32,402 --> 00:55:33,625
Well, let's head out first.

1442
00:55:33,625 --> 00:55:37,087
[The scenery around Boseong Station
feels somehow new]

1443
00:55:37,087 --> 00:55:38,811
Huh?

1444
00:55:39,737 --> 00:55:41,159
Huh?

1445
00:55:41,159 --> 00:55:43,747
[Director Choi gets excited
after receiving a greeting]

1446
00:55:43,747 --> 00:55:45,678
Wow, it's this cute and tiny?

1447
00:55:45,678 --> 00:55:47,654
- This town is really cute.
- I know, right?

1448
00:55:47,654 --> 00:55:49,187
[A different kind of quiet
and cozy feeling from Namwon]

1449
00:55:49,187 --> 00:55:50,780
Well, excuse me, just a second...

1450
00:55:50,780 --> 00:55:52,200
- Yeah.
- Wait a second, here...

1451
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:55,253
[Woo Shik turns Yumi and Seo Jun around...]

1452
00:55:55,253 --> 00:55:57,092
Please cross!

1453
00:55:57,715 --> 00:55:59,339
[Showing their professional side for a moment]

1454
00:55:59,339 --> 00:56:00,432
Cute!

1455
00:56:00,432 --> 00:56:05,065
[They head out of the station
full of excitement]

1456
00:56:05,065 --> 00:56:06,544
[Looking around]

1457
00:56:06,544 --> 00:56:09,080
It feels like we're in a miniature world.

1458
00:56:09,080 --> 00:56:10,726
Dae*** Tea Plantation?

1459
00:56:10,726 --> 00:56:11,959
Let me check.

1460
00:56:11,959 --> 00:56:14,992
First, let's see how long it takes
to get to Dae*** Tea Plantation.

1461
00:56:14,992 --> 00:56:17,621
Oh, there's a direct bus.

1462
00:56:18,457 --> 00:56:21,690
- What time is it now?
- It's 12:39, 12:40!

1463
00:56:21,690 --> 00:56:23,370
[Scanning the timetable]
12:39.

1464
00:56:23,370 --> 00:56:24,910
- There's one at 1 o'clock.
- 1 o'clock.

1465
00:56:24,910 --> 00:56:26,536
Should we wait for the bus?

1466
00:56:26,536 --> 00:56:28,717
It's 12:39, so waiting 20 minutes is fine.

1467
00:56:28,717 --> 00:56:30,656
[Nods]

1468
00:56:30,656 --> 00:56:33,291
- Where we are right now is...
- Here, Boseong Station.

1469
00:56:33,291 --> 00:56:34,691
- Ah.
- Everything is going down there.

1470
00:56:34,691 --> 00:56:36,948
[They gather together and check the map]

1471
00:56:36,948 --> 00:56:39,247
[Seo Jun's Plan 1, Visit the tea fields]
Go to Dae*** Tea Plantation first.

1472
00:56:39,247 --> 00:56:40,986
Look around a little,

1473
00:56:40,986 --> 00:56:43,691
- then take the bus... go there.
- Go to the beach.

1474
00:56:43,691 --> 00:56:45,891
- Then go to a guesthouse.
- I think we could just go to a guesthouse.

1475
00:56:45,891 --> 00:56:48,471
[Isn't that perfect?]
- Yeah. - Okay!

1476
00:56:48,471 --> 00:56:50,552
Hey, they have
seafood auction markets here too.

1477
00:56:50,552 --> 00:56:52,798
- Oh, true.
- This place might actually be way better.

1478
00:56:52,798 --> 00:56:54,479
Let's spend lunchtime here.

1479
00:56:54,479 --> 00:56:55,658
- Let's do that.
- Yeah.

1480
00:56:55,658 --> 00:56:58,840
Let's decide what to eat for dinner
and then find a guesthouse nearby.

1481
00:56:58,840 --> 00:57:00,853
[Everything goes smoothly]
- Yeah, here. - Yeah.

1482
00:57:00,853 --> 00:57:03,011
[11:59 AM, time to get on the bus]
But the line starts all the way over there.

1483
00:57:03,011 --> 00:57:05,758
- That's bad.
- Ah, this...

1484
00:57:05,758 --> 00:57:08,198
What if there aren't any seats?

1485
00:57:08,198 --> 00:57:09,744
- Oh my.
- Get in line.

1486
00:57:09,744 --> 00:57:11,277
[As the bus arrives]
Oh my.

1487
00:57:11,277 --> 00:57:13,846
[People start gathering all at once]
Miss, are you heading to the tea plantation?

1488
00:57:13,846 --> 00:57:15,653
Get in line!

1489
00:57:15,653 --> 00:57:16,893
[The trio slowly approaches too]

1490
00:57:16,893 --> 00:57:18,397
- This one?
- Yeah.

1491
00:57:18,397 --> 00:57:22,127
- Hello.
- We're riding the same bus.

1492
00:57:22,127 --> 00:57:25,067
[Successfully joined the line smoothly]
- You look amazing. - Thank you!

1493
00:57:25,067 --> 00:57:26,924
How much could it be?

1494
00:57:26,924 --> 00:57:29,527
- How much for three people?
- Yumi! It's 1,000 won each.

1495
00:57:29,527 --> 00:57:31,160
- Huh? Three thousand won!
- 1,000 won per person!

1496
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:32,241
- Oh, thank you.
- Okay.

1497
00:57:32,241 --> 00:57:34,014
- Thank you!
- Isn't it 1,000 won?

1498
00:57:34,014 --> 00:57:35,932
- 1,000 won.
- It's 1,000 won, right?

1499
00:57:35,932 --> 00:57:37,706
Oh my, your accent is so cute.

1500
00:57:37,706 --> 00:57:40,213
Oh dear, if it's not 1,000 won,
we're in trouble.

1501
00:57:40,213 --> 00:57:41,793
That's right, indeed it is.

1502
00:57:41,793 --> 00:57:43,513
- Sorry.
- They're cute.

1503
00:57:43,513 --> 00:57:44,825
[The trio has boarded]

1504
00:57:44,825 --> 00:57:45,855
Is it 1,000 won?

1505
00:57:45,855 --> 00:57:47,501
[Expense report, bus fare, -3,000 won]
Yeah, 3,000 won.

1506
00:57:47,501 --> 00:57:49,632
- Go ahead and pay.
- Thank you!

1507
00:57:49,632 --> 00:57:50,673
Should we go to the back?

1508
00:57:50,673 --> 00:57:52,073
- Yeah, let's go to the back.
- Sit in the last row?

1509
00:57:52,073 --> 00:57:53,164
- Can we sit here?
- Hello!

1510
00:57:53,164 --> 00:57:55,150
- Hello!
- Hello!

1511
00:57:55,150 --> 00:57:56,332
- Oh my, did you come here to film?
- Boseong...

1512
00:57:56,332 --> 00:57:58,605
- Yeah, we...
- Oh, we came for a trip.

1513
00:57:58,605 --> 00:57:59,658
[Laughing]

1514
00:57:59,658 --> 00:58:01,251
[The elderly locals warmly welcome them]
They're telling us to sit in the back.

1515
00:58:01,251 --> 00:58:03,481
- They're telling us to sit in the back.
- Move to the back? Let's go to the back.

1516
00:58:03,481 --> 00:58:06,858
- He's an actor too.
- Oh, your grandma?

1517
00:58:06,858 --> 00:58:08,168
Not my real grandma.

1518
00:58:08,168 --> 00:58:10,321
[The bus already feels warm and friendly]
Ah, yes.

1519
00:58:10,321 --> 00:58:12,782
She's so cute.

1520
00:58:12,782 --> 00:58:14,496
It's heavy, right?

1521
00:58:14,496 --> 00:58:16,046
No.

1522
00:58:16,046 --> 00:58:17,563
It's okay.

1523
00:58:17,563 --> 00:58:20,818
[The bus to the Boseong tea fields departs]

1524
00:58:22,093 --> 00:58:24,501
There are lots of young people!

1525
00:58:24,501 --> 00:58:27,235
- Young people?
- These are kids.

1526
00:58:27,235 --> 00:58:30,140
[Their age showed in their word choice]
- Young people are... - Kids, kids.

1527
00:58:30,140 --> 00:58:33,130
- Then what are we?
- We are youth!

1528
00:58:33,130 --> 00:58:34,877
- Youth?
- These are students here.

1529
00:58:34,877 --> 00:58:36,420
[Rebooting their youthful mindset once again]

1530
00:58:36,420 --> 00:58:37,712
Hey, friend!

1531
00:58:37,712 --> 00:58:39,420
- Are you from around here?
- Yeah!

1532
00:58:39,420 --> 00:58:41,415
What should we eat when we come here?

1533
00:58:41,415 --> 00:58:42,893
[Yum Quiz is starting up again after a while]

1534
00:58:42,893 --> 00:58:44,804
Is there somewhere here
that we absolutely have to visit?

1535
00:58:44,804 --> 00:58:46,700
[Asking the grandma sitting next to them]
Any famous restaurants in Yulpo?

1536
00:58:46,700 --> 00:58:49,007
- Gaetma***.
- Gaetma***! It's a raw fish restaurant though?

1537
00:58:49,007 --> 00:58:50,100
- Oh...
- Should I ask?

1538
00:58:50,100 --> 00:58:51,920
- Oh, it's a raw fish restaurant though?
- Yeah, it's a raw fish restaurant.

1539
00:58:51,920 --> 00:58:53,493
[Got a local spot rec right away]
Where? Gaet... Gaetma***?

1540
00:58:53,493 --> 00:58:54,754
- Gaetma***.
- Oh!

1541
00:58:54,754 --> 00:58:57,977
[Searching]
- Oh? - This looks good. Sliced raw fish.

1542
00:58:57,977 --> 00:58:59,733
Octopus soup!

1543
00:58:59,733 --> 00:59:01,380
Hey, after we save up a little, here...

1544
00:59:01,380 --> 00:59:02,645
- Should we feast on some raw fish?
- Raw fish...

1545
00:59:02,645 --> 00:59:03,980
- Let's do that.
- Sounds good.

1546
00:59:03,980 --> 00:59:06,005
[Saving lunch money
to eat raw fish for dinner!]

1547
00:59:06,005 --> 00:59:07,687
[However...]

1548
00:59:07,687 --> 00:59:09,380
- Aren't you hungry?
- Why is it...

1549
00:59:09,380 --> 00:59:12,195
Why does my stomach keep getting hungry
without any shame?

1550
00:59:12,195 --> 00:59:15,745
[And so, they move on hungry...]
Older people often have a lot of back pain...

1551
00:59:15,745 --> 00:59:18,600
This is a famous bread from Songjeong Station.

1552
00:59:18,600 --> 00:59:21,228
It's bread with a 60-year history.
Compare it to Daejeon bread.

1553
00:59:21,228 --> 00:59:23,352
- Can we really take this?
- Yeah, eat it.

1554
00:59:23,352 --> 00:59:25,306
We bought it for ourselves to eat.

1555
00:59:25,306 --> 00:59:27,252
- Ah, is this?
- But...

1556
00:59:27,252 --> 00:59:29,652
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1557
00:59:30,339 --> 00:59:32,111
He's such a "Teto guy."

1558
00:59:32,111 --> 00:59:33,832
My daughter was pregnant

1559
00:59:33,832 --> 00:59:35,670
and wanted bread from Daejeon,
so I went there, you know?

1560
00:59:35,670 --> 00:59:37,449
- Oh, so sweet.
- But...

1561
00:59:37,449 --> 00:59:38,876
- This bread tastes better.
- Yeah.

1562
00:59:38,876 --> 00:59:40,023
- Oh, really?
- Oh!

1563
00:59:40,023 --> 00:59:42,843
That's a 19-year-old bread
from Songjeong Station in Jeolla-do Province.

1564
00:59:42,843 --> 00:59:44,496
- As expected...
- It's over 50 years old.

1565
00:59:44,496 --> 00:59:46,264
- Oh!
- Oh! Thank you...

1566
00:59:46,264 --> 00:59:48,462
50-year-old Tto*** bread.

1567
00:59:48,462 --> 00:59:51,288
[Whether it's 19 or 50 years old,
it's definitely historic bread]

1568
00:59:51,288 --> 00:59:53,407
The bread is over a hundred years old.

1569
00:59:53,407 --> 00:59:54,841
A hundred years?

1570
00:59:54,841 --> 00:59:57,181
- You said 50 years earlier though?
- Oh...

1571
00:59:57,181 --> 00:59:58,954
Anyway, that bread is probably
over a hundred years old.

1572
00:59:58,954 --> 01:00:02,013
- Wow...
- Songjeong Station Market was founded in 1913.

1573
01:00:02,013 --> 01:00:04,699
- Oh, 1913...
- 1913? Wow.

1574
01:00:04,699 --> 01:00:05,754
[Just when exactly was this bread created...]

1575
01:00:05,754 --> 01:00:08,352
[Spoiler: Revealed in episode 5]

1576
01:00:08,352 --> 01:00:10,985
- Is it like garlic bread?
- Dae***...

1577
01:00:10,985 --> 01:00:12,105
No, a tea plantation.

1578
01:00:12,105 --> 01:00:13,272
Oh, Dae*** Tea Plantation.

1579
01:00:13,272 --> 01:00:14,559
[Anyway, they need to get off
at the Boseong Green Tea Field stop]

1580
01:00:14,559 --> 01:00:16,381
- There's no announcement though?
- Exactly.

1581
01:00:16,381 --> 01:00:18,167
- There's no route map either.
- Right.

1582
01:00:18,167 --> 01:00:19,860
Ma'am!

1583
01:00:19,860 --> 01:00:23,145
Excuse me, when should we get off
for Dae*** Tea Plantation?

1584
01:00:23,145 --> 01:00:24,532
I'll tell you when we get there.

1585
01:00:24,532 --> 01:00:25,572
Okay.

1586
01:00:25,572 --> 01:00:26,774
[Even grandma is radiating "Teto" energy]

1587
01:00:26,774 --> 01:00:28,707
Oh, thank you!

1588
01:00:28,707 --> 01:00:31,727
- I don't think we even need lunch today.
- Try this bread too. Here.

1589
01:00:31,727 --> 01:00:33,847
- No, it's okay.
- We have enough.

1590
01:00:33,847 --> 01:00:35,907
- This one too...
- Oh, my.

1591
01:00:35,907 --> 01:00:37,073
[Goal]
Oh, thank you so much!

1592
01:00:37,073 --> 01:00:38,746
[The "Teto" elder gives them
another precious bread]

1593
01:00:38,746 --> 01:00:41,832
- It would've been bad if we didn't take it.
- Oh, thank you!

1594
01:00:42,479 --> 01:00:43,639
Looks delicious.

1595
01:00:43,639 --> 01:00:44,962
[This time, the elder gives them
mugwort hotteok bread]

1596
01:00:44,962 --> 01:00:46,781
- This feels so warm and friendly.
- Maybe we're lucky with food today?

1597
01:00:46,781 --> 01:00:48,507
- Looks like it.
- Things just keep appearing.

1598
01:00:48,507 --> 01:00:50,913
But we have way too much food now.

1599
01:00:50,913 --> 01:00:55,878
[Today's food: garlic bread, mugwort hotteok
bread, Dubai Chewy Cookie, boiled eggs, etc...]

1600
01:00:55,878 --> 01:00:59,044
[The bus filled with warmth and kindness
keeps rolling on]

1601
01:00:59,044 --> 01:01:02,424
<i>The next stop is Dae*** Tea Plantation.</i>

1602
01:01:03,307 --> 01:01:04,753
Where are you headed?

1603
01:01:04,753 --> 01:01:06,276
- Dae*** Tea Plantation.
- Dae*** Tea Plantation!

1604
01:01:06,276 --> 01:01:10,053
- Then you need to get off here.
- We should get off here? Let's go!

1605
01:01:10,053 --> 01:01:11,878
- It was nice meeting you guys.
- Have fun!

1606
01:01:11,878 --> 01:01:13,473
- Thank you!
- Take care.

1607
01:01:13,473 --> 01:01:16,013
- Thank you. We'll enjoy the food.
- Take care!

1608
01:01:16,013 --> 01:01:18,559
- I'll buy you pen shells next time!
- Have a wonderful day today too.

1609
01:01:18,559 --> 01:01:20,025
[Getting off full of love and kindness]
Thank you!

1610
01:01:20,025 --> 01:01:22,915
- We'll enjoy the bread.
- Oh, thank you!

1611
01:01:22,915 --> 01:01:27,318
And the elder who gave us bread today...

1612
01:01:27,318 --> 01:01:28,964
He was cheerful and,

1613
01:01:28,964 --> 01:01:31,197
how should I put it...
really warm and friendly.

1614
01:01:31,197 --> 01:01:36,177
And I'm not totally sure,
but they seemed like a married couple.

1615
01:01:36,177 --> 01:01:39,124
But the way the two of them
talked to each other was so fun too.

1616
01:01:39,124 --> 01:01:42,627
[A heartfelt moment in Boseong]
It felt really heartwarming.

1617
01:01:42,627 --> 01:01:44,884
[To. Mr. Teto]
Oh, well...

1618
01:01:44,884 --> 01:01:47,625
Sir, in terms people use these days,

1619
01:01:47,625 --> 01:01:50,114
there's a term called "Teto guy."

1620
01:01:50,114 --> 01:01:53,172
You seem like the perfect
definition of a "Teto guy."

1621
01:01:53,172 --> 01:01:55,763
Yes, thanks to you, our trip

1622
01:01:55,763 --> 01:02:00,357
became filled with such sweet moments,
and we sincerely thank you for that.

1623
01:02:03,213 --> 01:02:07,705
Anyway, to get to Yulpo,
we need to take a bus from here.

1624
01:02:07,705 --> 01:02:09,552
There are buses throughout the day.

1625
01:02:09,552 --> 01:02:11,605
[Lots of buses headed to Yulpo Beach]

1626
01:02:11,605 --> 01:02:13,956
Anyway, there are buses at different times.

1627
01:02:13,956 --> 01:02:16,902
[They decide to come back here later!]
- Let's go. - Yeah, let's go check it out.

1628
01:02:16,902 --> 01:02:17,942
[1:20 PM / Entrance to
Boseong Green Tea Fields]

1629
01:02:17,942 --> 01:02:20,472
Go all the way up...

1630
01:02:20,472 --> 01:02:23,517
From here, I can't even tell
where the tea fields start.

1631
01:02:23,517 --> 01:02:26,777
- I think we need to keep going up that way.
- Right?

1632
01:02:26,777 --> 01:02:28,739
- This is the place!
- Oh, so this is it.

1633
01:02:28,739 --> 01:02:30,150
Ah, here it is!

1634
01:02:30,150 --> 01:02:32,672
[An extraordinary cedar tree path appears]

1635
01:02:33,747 --> 01:02:37,578
[A majestic cedar road
stretching toward the tea fields]

1636
01:02:37,578 --> 01:02:39,038
- Wow!
- Wow!

1637
01:02:39,038 --> 01:02:41,179
[Director Choi's camcorder ON]
Oh!

1638
01:02:41,179 --> 01:02:42,911
Ticket booth?

1639
01:02:44,935 --> 01:02:46,916
[Grin]

1640
01:02:48,399 --> 01:02:50,929
Wow, phytoncides!

1641
01:02:50,929 --> 01:02:52,429
[Breathes in]

1642
01:02:52,429 --> 01:02:54,673
Whoa!

1643
01:02:54,673 --> 01:02:56,328
The air feels so nice.

1644
01:02:56,328 --> 01:02:59,301
[The refreshing scent
spreading through the whole body]

1645
01:03:01,858 --> 01:03:03,668
Where are you going?

1646
01:03:06,763 --> 01:03:08,115
Careful with your hand.

1647
01:03:08,115 --> 01:03:11,935
[Suddenly acquired a giant walking stick]

1648
01:03:11,935 --> 01:03:15,363
- Answer, Gandalf!
- Yep, it's Gandalf.

1649
01:03:16,079 --> 01:03:18,105
Wow, this is really cool!

1650
01:03:19,842 --> 01:03:23,693
- We should take some pictures here.
- Yeah, let's take some pictures.

1651
01:03:23,693 --> 01:03:24,846
You go first.

1652
01:03:24,846 --> 01:03:25,943
[Capturing memories on a phone
for the first time in a while]

1653
01:03:25,943 --> 01:03:28,006
Oh, that looks good!

1654
01:03:28,006 --> 01:03:30,548
[#GandalfWooShik #YouShallNotPass]
Hey, you really look like Gandalf. Nice.

1655
01:03:31,195 --> 01:03:32,919
Next!

1656
01:03:34,572 --> 01:03:38,275
[#404 #NotFoundInTheSystem]

1657
01:03:38,275 --> 01:03:40,012
Next!

1658
01:03:42,518 --> 01:03:45,495
[#ForestBearPawSeoJun #Rawr]

1659
01:03:45,495 --> 01:03:46,516
Over here too...

1660
01:03:46,516 --> 01:03:48,845
- There's no ticket booth though?
- Oh, I think it's over there.

1661
01:03:48,845 --> 01:03:51,058
- Tickets? Here it is!
- The ticket booth.

1662
01:03:51,058 --> 01:03:52,099
- Oh, here it is!
- Yeah.

1663
01:03:52,099 --> 01:03:53,294
[Finally found the ticket booth]

1664
01:03:53,294 --> 01:03:54,324
Oh boy, oh boy.

1665
01:03:54,324 --> 01:03:55,943
Oh, yes!

1666
01:03:55,943 --> 01:03:58,117
[Ticket Office]
Three tickets for us, please.

1667
01:03:58,117 --> 01:04:00,380
- For three people, it's 12,000 won.
- Here you go.

1668
01:04:00,380 --> 01:04:02,269
[Expense report, Admission -12,000 won]
Yes, thank you.

1669
01:04:03,493 --> 01:04:07,912
[Finally, time to enter
the Boseong green tea fields!]

1670
01:04:07,912 --> 01:04:08,946
[Entering the Boseong Green Tea Fields]

1671
01:04:08,946 --> 01:04:10,251
Can we leave this here?

1672
01:04:10,251 --> 01:04:11,950
Oh!

1673
01:04:11,950 --> 01:04:14,488
[Found the storage lockers]

1674
01:04:14,488 --> 01:04:19,601
[Finally putting down all the luggage]

1675
01:04:19,601 --> 01:04:21,472
- A trip without bags.
- Let's go!

1676
01:04:21,472 --> 01:04:25,092
- Seriously, after two days...
- My shoulders feel so light.

1677
01:04:25,092 --> 01:04:26,972
- To the tea fields?
- Go, go!

1678
01:04:26,972 --> 01:04:28,878
To the tea fields!

1679
01:04:32,589 --> 01:04:34,054
The matcha ice cream looks delicious.

1680
01:04:34,054 --> 01:04:36,176
Let's ask.

1681
01:04:36,176 --> 01:04:39,149
[An eye-catching matcha ice cream sign]
- Isn't this that thing? - It looks so good.

1682
01:04:39,149 --> 01:04:40,882
4,500 won!

1683
01:04:41,502 --> 01:04:43,208
Looks delicious.

1684
01:04:43,208 --> 01:04:45,155
Hey, let's try that later.

1685
01:04:46,291 --> 01:04:49,774
- Wow, how do we even climb this?
- Whoa...

1686
01:04:49,774 --> 01:04:51,518
[What unfolded before the trio is...]

1687
01:04:51,518 --> 01:04:53,404
I don't even ride those things.

1688
01:04:53,404 --> 01:04:56,393
- The tea fields must be worth seeing.
- Yeah.

1689
01:04:56,393 --> 01:04:58,065
[A massive stairway to heaven]
- Let's go. - Let's go.

1690
01:04:58,065 --> 01:04:59,737
- We're here now, right?
- Yeah.

1691
01:04:59,737 --> 01:05:02,478
- Yumi, you can do it.
- Yeah, I can do it.

1692
01:05:02,478 --> 01:05:04,649
Let's go!

1693
01:05:04,649 --> 01:05:06,864
[First time climbing Boseong tea fields]

1694
01:05:06,864 --> 01:05:10,067
- It's huge.
- This is literally a stairway to heaven.

1695
01:05:10,067 --> 01:05:11,957
Wow!

1696
01:05:11,957 --> 01:05:13,917
- This really works your legs.
- Man, this is no joke for me.

1697
01:05:13,917 --> 01:05:16,271
Wait, should we go step by step?
Or take two steps at once?

1698
01:05:16,271 --> 01:05:17,324
- One at a time.
- I do two at a time.

1699
01:05:17,324 --> 01:05:19,757
- You're taking two at a time right now?
- No.

1700
01:05:19,757 --> 01:05:22,858
- I can't. My legs aren't long enough.
- Alright, let's take it slow.

1701
01:05:24,462 --> 01:05:28,424
- The color isn't super green right now.
- Right, it's still winter, isn't it?

1702
01:05:28,424 --> 01:05:29,512
[Filming Date: Feb 26,
tea fields in winter off-season]

1703
01:05:29,512 --> 01:05:33,030
- Still, this is pretty good for winter.
- The leaves are falling and...

1704
01:05:33,679 --> 01:05:37,392
[Fun Fact: Winter dormancy (Nov-Mar),
tea leaves appear dull green]

1705
01:05:37,392 --> 01:05:41,378
[Apr-May, fresh sprouts grow
and turn fields light green]

1706
01:05:41,378 --> 01:05:42,903
- Oh, it's hot though?
- Hold on, I've got altitude sickness...

1707
01:05:42,903 --> 01:05:45,316
- Let's go rest over there for a second.
- We're almost there.

1708
01:05:45,316 --> 01:05:48,782
- My ears feel blocked.
- I've got altitude sickness...

1709
01:05:50,038 --> 01:05:52,316
[Arrived at the central observatory]

1710
01:05:54,991 --> 01:05:57,059
This is incredible!

1711
01:05:58,191 --> 01:06:01,579
[A refreshing green tea landscape
that cools you to the core]

1712
01:06:01,579 --> 01:06:04,335
Seriously, it feels like
even my lungs are getting healthier.

1713
01:06:04,335 --> 01:06:06,607
Yes, it's a real workout. Seriously.

1714
01:06:06,607 --> 01:06:10,302
[A precious time in every healthy way!]
- Right, you too! Me too! - It's good exercise.

1715
01:06:10,302 --> 01:06:11,552
- Let's go!
- Let's keep going.

1716
01:06:11,552 --> 01:06:12,633
Should we head up first?

1717
01:06:12,633 --> 01:06:14,570
[Deciding to check out the other side too!]

1718
01:06:15,425 --> 01:06:17,826
- Oh? We could do that here.
- Do what?

1719
01:06:17,826 --> 01:06:19,205
The camera stays still,

1720
01:06:19,205 --> 01:06:22,072
- and you hide over there, and here too.
- Like this?

1721
01:06:22,072 --> 01:06:24,798
[Planning a bush jump-out scene]
Right? Let's try that.

1722
01:06:24,798 --> 01:06:29,713
Right here, we can shoot
a t-t-trailer... trailer here.

1723
01:06:29,713 --> 01:06:32,089
[Director Choi even starts directing a teaser]
Yeah, a teaser.

1724
01:06:32,089 --> 01:06:33,276
Oh, I think we can film it here.

1725
01:06:33,276 --> 01:06:34,875
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1726
01:06:34,875 --> 01:06:38,774
- Here, how did they get in here earlier?
- I think this spot gives the best front angle.

1727
01:06:38,774 --> 01:06:40,843
Sit down, then try standing up.

1728
01:06:41,672 --> 01:06:43,639
One, two, three!

1729
01:06:43,639 --> 01:06:46,567
[Looks like they can come up one by one]
And then appear from behind, one by one.

1730
01:06:46,567 --> 01:06:48,065
- I'll go over there for a sec.
- Okay.

1731
01:06:48,065 --> 01:06:50,132
[Scurrying off]

1732
01:06:50,132 --> 01:06:52,078
[Director Choi fearlessly scouting locations]

1733
01:06:52,078 --> 01:06:54,022
Is there another path?

1734
01:06:55,865 --> 01:06:57,785
There's another path over there.

1735
01:06:59,625 --> 01:07:03,431
[But how far are you going, Director Choi?]
Hey, I can't see the path from here.

1736
01:07:03,431 --> 01:07:05,676
- Isn't that too far?
- It is too far. Way too far.

1737
01:07:05,676 --> 01:07:08,109
[The obedient youngest member]

1738
01:07:08,109 --> 01:07:09,423
Yeah, Seo Jun, stay there.

1739
01:07:09,423 --> 01:07:11,045
- Me here?
- I'll stand in the middle here.

1740
01:07:11,045 --> 01:07:13,428
But what if I'm not visible?
Do I look too small?

1741
01:07:13,428 --> 01:07:15,395
- Take a look.
- Can't you see me?

1742
01:07:15,395 --> 01:07:17,208
- Am I showing up?
- Yeah, you show up well.

1743
01:07:17,208 --> 01:07:19,601
What about Seo Jun? Can you see him?

1744
01:07:19,601 --> 01:07:21,101
[Seo Jun's position all good]

1745
01:07:21,101 --> 01:07:22,966
Can't you see me at first?

1746
01:07:22,966 --> 01:07:24,308
Then who comes out first?

1747
01:07:24,308 --> 01:07:25,448
- You go first, Yumi.
- You go first.

1748
01:07:25,448 --> 01:07:27,141
Me first?

1749
01:07:27,141 --> 01:07:28,534
Ouch!

1750
01:07:28,534 --> 01:07:32,159
[Standby complete]

1751
01:07:32,159 --> 01:07:34,137
Start!

1752
01:07:34,137 --> 01:07:35,929
Ta-da!

1753
01:07:36,808 --> 01:07:37,756
Youth Over...

1754
01:07:37,756 --> 01:07:40,520
- Flowers!
- Flowers!

1755
01:07:40,520 --> 01:07:44,567
[Refreshing smile]

1756
01:07:45,567 --> 01:07:48,114
- Alright, good work, everyone.
- Good work!

1757
01:07:48,114 --> 01:07:49,360
Wait, is this right?

1758
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:51,487
Why does saying "Youth" feel so awkward?

1759
01:07:52,420 --> 01:07:54,044
- Alright, shall we head down now?
- Let's head down...

1760
01:07:54,044 --> 01:07:56,947
[For "Youths," their energy
is completely drained]

1761
01:07:56,947 --> 01:07:58,930
I'm really curious about green tea ice cream.

1762
01:07:58,930 --> 01:08:01,172
Since we're here, I really want to try it.

1763
01:08:01,172 --> 01:08:02,323
Wow, here it is.

1764
01:08:02,323 --> 01:08:05,543
- Let's try the ice cream.
- That's cedar. Cedar trees.

1765
01:08:05,543 --> 01:08:09,989
[Receipt, Matcha Ice Cream, 4,500 won]
One matcha ice cream in a cup,

1766
01:08:09,989 --> 01:08:12,535
[Receipt, Boseong Green Tea (hot) 3,000 won]
and one hot green tea, please.

1767
01:08:12,535 --> 01:08:13,907
Affogato, let's go.

1768
01:08:13,907 --> 01:08:18,540
[Receipt, Matcha Affogato 5,000 won]
One Boseong matcha affogato, please.

1769
01:08:18,540 --> 01:08:19,940
- 12,500 won?
- Yes.

1770
01:08:19,940 --> 01:08:22,433
[Expense report, Green Tea Snacks: -12,500 won,
Remaining Balance: 267,210 won]

1771
01:08:22,433 --> 01:08:23,881
Thank you! Oh, yes.

1772
01:08:23,881 --> 01:08:25,870
[What will green tea from Boseong taste like?]

1773
01:08:25,870 --> 01:08:28,332
- Affogato.
- Let's each try some together.

1774
01:08:28,332 --> 01:08:30,615
- Okay... then should I try this first?
- This one!

1775
01:08:30,615 --> 01:08:32,065
- Okay!
- Okay!

1776
01:08:32,065 --> 01:08:33,832
You try first, Yumi.

1777
01:08:34,535 --> 01:08:38,054
[Oldest Yumi takes a spoonful]

1778
01:08:39,168 --> 01:08:40,774
[Yum!]

1779
01:08:40,774 --> 01:08:42,209
- It's kind of bitter?
- Yeah.

1780
01:08:42,209 --> 01:08:43,707
- Sweet and bitter?
- Yeah.

1781
01:08:43,707 --> 01:08:45,520
Really, seriously.

1782
01:08:46,408 --> 01:08:47,701
- Oh, it's good.
- Yeah.

1783
01:08:47,701 --> 01:08:48,793
Yeah.

1784
01:08:48,793 --> 01:08:51,975
It kinda feels like in my mouth...

1785
01:08:51,975 --> 01:08:54,324
Boseong itself entered my mouth.

1786
01:08:54,324 --> 01:08:56,526
[Jeez...]

1787
01:08:58,328 --> 01:09:00,807
- What is this? Yogurt?
- It's affogato.

1788
01:09:00,807 --> 01:09:02,338
- You have to eat the bottom part too.
- Try it with the bottom part.

1789
01:09:02,338 --> 01:09:04,614
The top part's good too. Try the top first.

1790
01:09:04,614 --> 01:09:06,417
[A big spoonful starting from the top]
The white part.

1791
01:09:06,417 --> 01:09:07,983
Does this just taste like milk?

1792
01:09:07,983 --> 01:09:10,208
- No, it's like mixed with milk.
- Huh? Why is the milk flavor so rich?

1793
01:09:10,208 --> 01:09:11,496
Right? It's kinda interesting.

1794
01:09:11,496 --> 01:09:14,094
This milk ice cream kinda tastes like...

1795
01:09:14,094 --> 01:09:15,481
- that milk from vending machines.
- Yeah, yeah!

1796
01:09:15,481 --> 01:09:16,707
Wow!

1797
01:09:16,707 --> 01:09:18,327
That milk from vending machines.

1798
01:09:18,327 --> 01:09:19,774
[Rich flavor, genuine reactions]
Wow!

1799
01:09:19,774 --> 01:09:20,781
That's exactly it.

1800
01:09:20,781 --> 01:09:23,088
- I'll try the green tea.
- You try it.

1801
01:09:23,088 --> 01:09:24,466
[Today's highlight: Boseong green tea,
fresh from the source]

1802
01:09:24,466 --> 01:09:27,074
- Oh, this milk is really tasty.
- Yeah.

1803
01:09:28,754 --> 01:09:30,313
- I should've tried this first.
- Why is that?

1804
01:09:30,313 --> 01:09:32,246
I can't taste it anymore.

1805
01:09:34,026 --> 01:09:36,133
[Nodding in agreement]
You know what I mean, right?

1806
01:09:36,133 --> 01:09:38,122
Because we had something
too strong before this.

1807
01:09:38,122 --> 01:09:40,490
You guys totally had these in the wrong order.

1808
01:09:40,490 --> 01:09:43,307
[Woo Shik takes a sip too]

1809
01:09:43,307 --> 01:09:44,892
It just tastes like hot water right now.

1810
01:09:44,892 --> 01:09:47,637
It just tastes like hot water right now.

1811
01:09:47,637 --> 01:09:49,353
I can't taste anything.

1812
01:09:49,353 --> 01:09:50,806
It's just hot water.

1813
01:09:50,806 --> 01:09:53,849
[Viewers, please drink the green tea first...]
Yeah, it's hot water.

1814
01:09:53,849 --> 01:09:55,546
We didn't think about that.

1815
01:09:56,426 --> 01:09:57,952
- Honestly, I...
- Yeah.

1816
01:09:57,952 --> 01:10:00,217
I actually like this more than the ice cream.

1817
01:10:00,217 --> 01:10:02,306
[The rich flavor of Boseong green tea kicks in]
Wow, this is really good.

1818
01:10:02,306 --> 01:10:05,372
- Oh, it steeped more.
- Yeah.

1819
01:10:05,372 --> 01:10:06,936
This green tea is seriously different!

1820
01:10:06,936 --> 01:10:08,125
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1821
01:10:08,125 --> 01:10:11,779
It's much stronger than the green tea bags
we usually drink.

1822
01:10:11,779 --> 01:10:13,985
- Yeah, that's definitely true.
- Yeah.

1823
01:10:13,985 --> 01:10:17,389
But, you know those big clumps
of green tea leaves?

1824
01:10:17,389 --> 01:10:21,069
So those are all individually picked
and made into this, right?

1825
01:10:21,069 --> 01:10:22,929
Those are the fresh sprouts!

1826
01:10:22,929 --> 01:10:25,838
- Fresh sprouts!
- Like tender young leaves.

1827
01:10:25,838 --> 01:10:27,638
Yeah, but there's a specific season for that.

1828
01:10:27,638 --> 01:10:30,484
- Oh, so those aren't the ones, huh?
- No, those are it. Those are...

1829
01:10:30,484 --> 01:10:33,688
Even though it's winter now,
there's a season when new leaves grow.

1830
01:10:33,688 --> 01:10:35,001
They pick those, and...

1831
01:10:35,001 --> 01:10:37,782
- So they pick the young leaves?
- Yeah, the young leaves.

1832
01:10:37,782 --> 01:10:40,267
[As they spend a relaxing time with green tea]
That's not allowed. That's forbidden.

1833
01:10:40,267 --> 01:10:43,088
You should just try it once
right before retirement too.

1834
01:10:43,687 --> 01:10:45,154
[A cute couple completely
obsessed with rock-paper-scissors]

1835
01:10:45,154 --> 01:10:46,931
Wow...

1836
01:10:46,931 --> 01:10:49,537
Hey, I just saw it live. They're climbing up
playing rock-paper-scissors.

1837
01:10:49,537 --> 01:10:50,772
- Oh, my.
- No way!

1838
01:10:50,772 --> 01:10:53,236
- They started all the way from the bottom.
- Wow...

1839
01:10:53,236 --> 01:10:55,622
- Wow.
- Quick, film it, hurry!

1840
01:10:55,622 --> 01:10:57,157
- Wow, that's...
- Oh, my!

1841
01:10:57,157 --> 01:10:58,765
There were so many comebacks and reversals.

1842
01:10:58,765 --> 01:11:01,666
[Unlike a certain someone...]
- Oh, really? - You didn't film it?

1843
01:11:01,666 --> 01:11:04,531
[Climbing the hill
without even noticing how hard it is]

1844
01:11:04,531 --> 01:11:08,672
[The love-filled rock-paper-scissors couple...]

1845
01:11:08,672 --> 01:11:11,065
- Are they gonna hit each other now?
- What are they gonna do?

1846
01:11:11,065 --> 01:11:13,016
So what does the winner do?

1847
01:11:13,016 --> 01:11:15,282
- Do they get a hug?
- What does the winner do?

1848
01:11:15,282 --> 01:11:16,980
[30s-40s getting excited over young love...]
Piggyback rides!

1849
01:11:16,980 --> 01:11:18,779
- Ah...
- The guy's super tall!

1850
01:11:18,779 --> 01:11:20,695
So annoying.

1851
01:11:22,720 --> 01:11:24,911
[Such contrasting situations...]

1852
01:11:24,911 --> 01:11:26,879
Yumi, did you ever do
stuff like that while dating?

1853
01:11:26,879 --> 01:11:28,195
Do you think I have?

1854
01:11:28,195 --> 01:11:31,828
- Dig deep into your memories.
- Ah, it's all blurry now.

1855
01:11:31,828 --> 01:11:34,201
- Ah, I haven't done it.
- Really?

1856
01:11:34,201 --> 01:11:36,810
Park Seo Jun, you really never did?
Did you do it in college or not?

1857
01:11:36,810 --> 01:11:38,404
- I seriously haven't.
- Oh...

1858
01:11:38,404 --> 01:11:40,224
- Woo Shik, have you done it?
- Back in school, with friends...

1859
01:11:40,224 --> 01:11:41,458
I have.

1860
01:11:41,458 --> 01:11:43,679
- So you have?
- With your girlfriend?

1861
01:11:43,679 --> 01:11:45,495
Was it nice?

1862
01:11:45,495 --> 01:11:47,095
I was happy back then.

1863
01:11:47,095 --> 01:11:48,848
[The mood suddenly turns sentimental]

1864
01:11:48,848 --> 01:11:51,326
- Yeah?
- That's the right answer.

1865
01:11:51,326 --> 01:11:52,524
I used to win rock-paper-scissors...

1866
01:11:52,524 --> 01:11:55,642
and when I got reversed and lost,
it still felt really happy.

1867
01:11:55,642 --> 01:11:57,253
We'd just laugh and laugh.

1868
01:11:57,253 --> 01:12:00,170
After rock-paper-scissors, you gotta give them
a piggyback ride at the end.

1869
01:12:00,170 --> 01:12:02,412
[An experienced veteran with endless stories]

1870
01:12:02,412 --> 01:12:04,110
Then have you ever carried someone?

1871
01:12:04,110 --> 01:12:06,684
- Given someone a piggyback ride? Me?
- Probably have.

1872
01:12:09,191 --> 01:12:11,546
I guess there was.

1873
01:12:11,546 --> 01:12:12,698
There was, right?

1874
01:12:12,698 --> 01:12:14,771
Oh, yeah, I have. I've given piggyback rides.

1875
01:12:14,771 --> 01:12:16,637
I've carried people a lot. All the time.

1876
01:12:16,637 --> 01:12:19,044
- You? Oh, not you being carried?
- Of course.

1877
01:12:19,044 --> 01:12:20,811
[Po-po still can't let go of her doubts]

1878
01:12:20,811 --> 01:12:23,688
If you... if you date me,

1879
01:12:23,688 --> 01:12:25,064
your legs get thinner.

1880
01:12:25,064 --> 01:12:26,085
All lies. Total nonsense.

1881
01:12:26,085 --> 01:12:28,423
So when I put her down
after a piggyback ride, like this...

1882
01:12:28,423 --> 01:12:31,304
[Like a newborn giraffe]

1883
01:12:31,956 --> 01:12:34,437
- Because it's been so long.
- It's been so long...

1884
01:12:34,437 --> 01:12:36,516
since she's actually touched the ground.

1885
01:12:37,475 --> 01:12:40,948
[Ending with questionable love stories...]
What time is it? You finished everything?

1886
01:12:40,948 --> 01:12:42,433
Yeah.

1887
01:12:42,433 --> 01:12:44,120
- But are you giving us three?
- Pick one each.

1888
01:12:44,120 --> 01:12:45,140
- You each take one.
- One per person.

1889
01:12:45,140 --> 01:12:46,710
What is it?

1890
01:12:46,710 --> 01:12:49,623
- Then when Yumi comes, from among these...
- Shopping bag?

1891
01:12:49,623 --> 01:12:51,091
We can ditch the Daiso bag now.

1892
01:12:51,091 --> 01:12:53,304
- Oh, Daiso... huh?
- Huh? That's right.

1893
01:12:53,304 --> 01:12:54,444
- How big is this?
- Yeah.

1894
01:12:54,444 --> 01:12:56,130
How big is this?

1895
01:12:56,130 --> 01:12:57,177
One per 50,000 won...

1896
01:12:57,177 --> 01:12:58,603
Wow, this is enough.

1897
01:12:58,603 --> 01:13:00,177
- That's enough, definitely enough.
- Wow.

1898
01:13:00,177 --> 01:13:01,556
[Finally freed from paper bags]

1899
01:13:01,556 --> 01:13:04,739
- Seo Jun, it's kind of past lunch time.
- Yeah, it is.

1900
01:13:04,739 --> 01:13:06,035
So while we wait for the bus...

1901
01:13:06,035 --> 01:13:07,571
let's eat the bread we got earlier

1902
01:13:07,571 --> 01:13:11,995
- and eat the eggs too at the bus stop.
- Okay.

1903
01:13:11,995 --> 01:13:14,957
[2:50 PM / Entrance to
the Boseong Green Tea Fields]

1904
01:13:16,175 --> 01:13:17,487
Huh? The bus?

1905
01:13:17,487 --> 01:13:18,561
Did it pass already?

1906
01:13:18,561 --> 01:13:20,474
- Oh, no!
- Is that it?

1907
01:13:21,158 --> 01:13:24,381
[They miss the bus right in front of them]
- No way... - Ah, one just left.

1908
01:13:24,381 --> 01:13:26,691
[So close...]

1909
01:13:26,691 --> 01:13:28,887
Oh, that's lucky. At the bus stop...

1910
01:13:28,887 --> 01:13:31,388
- Guess we have time to eat now.
- We've got time to eat the eggs now.

1911
01:13:31,388 --> 01:13:34,647
- What a relief.
- Ah, my legs.

1912
01:13:34,647 --> 01:13:37,754
- This spot is perfect.
- Let me just check the time.

1913
01:13:37,754 --> 01:13:39,574
There's one at 3:25.

1914
01:13:39,574 --> 01:13:40,760
What time is it now?

1915
01:13:40,760 --> 01:13:42,094
- It's 3 o'clock.
- 3 o'clock?

1916
01:13:42,094 --> 01:13:45,048
[Exactly 25 minutes left]
- Oh, perfect. - Perfect timing.

1917
01:13:45,048 --> 01:13:46,895
- Yumi, should we sit over there?
- Yeah, sounds good.

1918
01:13:46,895 --> 01:13:49,052
[Now they need to find a place to eat lunch...]

1919
01:13:49,052 --> 01:13:51,550
[Taxi Stand]
- Okay. Let's wait for a taxi. - Oh, yeah!

1920
01:13:51,550 --> 01:13:53,165
Huh? This is actually a shelter.

1921
01:13:53,165 --> 01:13:55,489
- Come here, how about this place?
- Traveler Shelter?

1922
01:13:55,489 --> 01:13:57,268
- Yeah. Traveler Shelter.
- Oh, it is!

1923
01:13:57,268 --> 01:13:59,336
[The staff discovered a Traveler Shelter]
We'll wait here.

1924
01:13:59,336 --> 01:14:01,879
- Huh? But there's a password lock.
- Is it locked?

1925
01:14:01,879 --> 01:14:04,861
[It opened!]
Does it open? Okay!

1926
01:14:07,535 --> 01:14:09,692
[What will the inside look like?]

1927
01:14:09,692 --> 01:14:11,987
Wow, this is nice. Oh my.

1928
01:14:11,987 --> 01:14:13,934
Wow, a place like this exists?

1929
01:14:14,604 --> 01:14:16,719
- This is nice.
- No way, this makes no sense.

1930
01:14:16,719 --> 01:14:19,953
- Wow, the facilities are nice.
- This place is...

1931
01:14:19,953 --> 01:14:21,827
Why does this keep happening to us?

1932
01:14:21,827 --> 01:14:23,793
We finally get to eat the eggs.

1933
01:14:23,793 --> 01:14:26,739
[Eggs eaten only half a day after being boiled]

1934
01:14:26,739 --> 01:14:28,780
I wonder how that highly praised bread tastes.

1935
01:14:28,780 --> 01:14:31,591
He said you'd have to wait
50 years in line for this.

1936
01:14:31,591 --> 01:14:34,711
[Will it really be worth a 50-year wait?]

1937
01:14:34,711 --> 01:14:36,784
Wow, the smell is incredible.

1938
01:14:37,627 --> 01:14:40,051
- Yeah, it's garlic.
- Yeah.

1939
01:14:41,265 --> 01:14:42,665
What should we eat first...

1940
01:14:42,665 --> 01:14:44,072
[The happy dilemma of what to eat first]

1941
01:14:44,072 --> 01:14:46,366
Let's crack the egg first!

1942
01:14:46,366 --> 01:14:52,343
[Tapping the eggshell lightly]

1943
01:14:52,343 --> 01:14:54,234
[Quickly peeling off the shells]

1944
01:14:54,234 --> 01:14:57,480
- You're really good at peeling them.
- Guess I got lucky.

1945
01:14:57,480 --> 01:15:00,407
- Wow, these boiled perfectly.
- Who boiled them?

1946
01:15:01,331 --> 01:15:02,611
The hot water did.

1947
01:15:02,611 --> 01:15:03,779
[Takes a bite while giving
a totally unrelated answer]

1948
01:15:03,779 --> 01:15:06,592
- Oh, it peeled really well.
- Whoa!

1949
01:15:08,386 --> 01:15:09,861
[Take a big bite]
I'm spilling it everywhere.

1950
01:15:09,861 --> 01:15:12,846
[Spotless]

1951
01:15:12,846 --> 01:15:14,373
[Yum]

1952
01:15:16,466 --> 01:15:18,252
The eggs are good too!

1953
01:15:19,081 --> 01:15:20,927
Anyone got salt?

1954
01:15:21,594 --> 01:15:24,000
Should I run around a bit and get some?

1955
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:26,546
[Human salt mine]

1956
01:15:27,334 --> 01:15:28,446
Next!

1957
01:15:28,446 --> 01:15:30,393
[Moving along quickly]

1958
01:15:30,393 --> 01:15:32,272
Let me try it.

1959
01:15:32,963 --> 01:15:36,878
[Finally, time to taste
Teto guy's garlic bread]

1960
01:15:41,997 --> 01:15:43,643
This is good!

1961
01:15:43,643 --> 01:15:45,600
This is really good.

1962
01:15:45,600 --> 01:15:48,537
- Oh, the inside tastes even better.
- Yeah?

1963
01:15:48,537 --> 01:15:49,891
- Wow, this looks amazing.
- It's good.

1964
01:15:49,891 --> 01:15:52,555
How is it? Is it worth a 50-year wait?

1965
01:15:52,555 --> 01:15:54,030
[Obviously]
It's delicious.

1966
01:15:54,030 --> 01:15:56,990
Wow. This is the real deal.

1967
01:15:58,722 --> 01:16:00,577
- It's moist.
- Yum!

1968
01:16:00,577 --> 01:16:03,843
But that older gentleman
who gave us the bread earlier...

1969
01:16:03,843 --> 01:16:05,005
wasn't he super sweet?

1970
01:16:05,005 --> 01:16:06,031
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1971
01:16:06,031 --> 01:16:07,591
His daughter was pregnant, so he went...

1972
01:16:07,591 --> 01:16:08,768
- His daughter.
- Yeah, his daughter.

1973
01:16:08,768 --> 01:16:10,212
He even went all the way to Seong***dang.

1974
01:16:10,212 --> 01:16:12,141
[So sweet]

1975
01:16:12,141 --> 01:16:15,152
He casually tossed the bread over like,
"Here, eat."

1976
01:16:15,152 --> 01:16:16,962
[The Teto guy made quite an impression]

1977
01:16:16,962 --> 01:16:17,964
"Teto guy."

1978
01:16:17,964 --> 01:16:18,997
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1979
01:16:18,997 --> 01:16:20,710
[After finishing their simple lunch...]

1980
01:16:20,710 --> 01:16:22,153
It's here!

1981
01:16:22,153 --> 01:16:25,281
[Soon after, the 3:25 bus arrives]

1982
01:16:27,123 --> 01:16:29,349
- Three of us, paying cash.
- Yeah.

1983
01:16:29,349 --> 01:16:33,279
[Boarding complete]
- How many stops to Yulpo? - Six.

1984
01:16:33,279 --> 01:16:36,219
[No seats this time, so they ride standing up]

1985
01:16:36,219 --> 01:16:38,033
We're heading to Yulpo.

1986
01:16:38,033 --> 01:16:39,606
Grandma, are you going to Yulpo too?

1987
01:16:39,606 --> 01:16:41,742
- We're going past Yulpo.
- Oh, really?

1988
01:16:41,742 --> 01:16:42,948
Then could you let us know

1989
01:16:42,948 --> 01:16:44,677
- when we should get off for Yulpo?
- Yes.

1990
01:16:44,677 --> 01:16:47,555
[Just as they thought Yumi's chatting
made the ride easier...]

1991
01:16:49,558 --> 01:16:52,458
[Entering a sharp curve]

1992
01:16:53,058 --> 01:16:55,325
[The bus is tilting]

1993
01:16:55,325 --> 01:16:57,710
- What? What's going on?
- What is this, hold on...

1994
01:16:57,710 --> 01:17:00,246
- My back hurts so much.
- Wait, these curves... Hold on.

1995
01:17:00,246 --> 01:17:01,896
[These curves, hold on...]
Hold on.

1996
01:17:01,896 --> 01:17:03,497
[This time, a right curve]

1997
01:17:03,497 --> 01:17:05,042
Oh, it just turns like this.

1998
01:17:05,042 --> 01:17:07,248
[Twisting and turning]
Oh my gosh.

1999
01:17:07,248 --> 01:17:08,602
Oh man, I'm seriously struggling right now.

2000
01:17:08,602 --> 01:17:10,442
[Their journey is anything but smooth]

2001
01:17:10,442 --> 01:17:13,822
<i>This stop is Yulpo.</i>

2002
01:17:13,822 --> 01:17:16,008
They're really developing this place.

2003
01:17:16,008 --> 01:17:18,795
[Yulpo feels more deserted than expected]
But is today some kind of holiday?

2004
01:17:18,795 --> 01:17:19,869
It's the off-season.

2005
01:17:19,869 --> 01:17:23,830
- Seo Jun, but the guesthouses aren't cheap.
- How much?

2006
01:17:23,830 --> 01:17:25,624
- 160,000 won.
- What?

2007
01:17:25,624 --> 01:17:27,454
Closed today?

2008
01:17:27,454 --> 01:17:28,945
[Everywhere they go]
Oh, guesthouse inquiries.

2009
01:17:28,945 --> 01:17:30,637
[Closed today]
- Closed today. - This place is closed too?

2010
01:17:30,637 --> 01:17:32,106
[Where on earth are we supposed to sleep...]
Oh dear.

2011
01:17:32,106 --> 01:17:34,198
- Wow, there are so many.
- Oh dear, oh dear.

2012
01:17:34,198 --> 01:17:37,442
- Let's keep going for now.
- We might have to sleep outside.

2013
01:17:37,442 --> 01:17:41,287
[A Boseong trip as vast as the open sea,
coming soon]

2014
01:17:41,287 --> 01:17:43,297
[Next week]

2015
01:17:43,297 --> 01:17:45,957
[Three arrive at a fish center in Boseong]
Wow, that must be super fresh.

2016
01:17:45,957 --> 01:17:47,450
What should we eat?

2017
01:17:47,450 --> 01:17:49,329
- Striped beakfish is delicious.
- Should we get striped beakfish?

2018
01:17:49,329 --> 01:17:51,271
[After picking some hefty ones]
This one.

2019
01:17:51,271 --> 01:17:54,193
- It comes to about 140,000 to 150,000 won.
- Yeah.

2020
01:17:54,193 --> 01:17:55,601
[Just go for it]

2021
01:17:55,601 --> 01:17:56,555
It's here!

2022
01:17:56,555 --> 01:17:58,460
- Wow.
- The expensive one!

2023
01:17:58,460 --> 01:18:00,446
[After saving and saving, finally tasting it]
Let's just try the raw fish first.

2024
01:18:00,446 --> 01:18:02,599
[Raw fish feels especially meaningful]

2025
01:18:02,599 --> 01:18:04,098
We really splurged today.

2026
01:18:04,098 --> 01:18:05,732
[And the next day...]

2027
01:18:05,732 --> 01:18:07,320
[The airport?]

2028
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:09,936
We're trying to get to the airport,
how do we get there?

2029
01:18:09,936 --> 01:18:11,962
[They had a hidden goal all along]

2030
01:18:11,962 --> 01:18:14,738
Or should we seriously do a day trip to Jeju?

2031
01:18:14,738 --> 01:18:16,505
Let's just go straight to Jeju.

2032
01:18:16,505 --> 01:18:17,999
- Gwangju International Airport?
- Yeah, from here...

2033
01:18:17,999 --> 01:18:20,112
[A spontaneous trip to Jeju]
We're trying to go to Jeju today.

2034
01:18:20,112 --> 01:18:21,672
So are we drinking Hallasan soju tonight?

2035
01:18:21,672 --> 01:18:22,906
[Sounds so good]

2036
01:18:22,906 --> 01:18:24,605
Jeju should be warm, right?

2037
01:18:24,605 --> 01:18:26,425
[Their hearts are already at Hallasan]
This is about to get fun.

2038
01:18:26,425 --> 01:18:28,626
But it's not over until it's over.

2039
01:18:28,626 --> 01:18:29,629
Where's the airport?

2040
01:18:29,629 --> 01:18:31,237
Why is there seriously nothing here?

2041
01:18:31,237 --> 01:18:32,566
Is this the right place?

2042
01:18:32,566 --> 01:18:34,746
[No airport anywhere?]
Seriously, why is there nothing here though?

2043
01:18:34,746 --> 01:18:36,073
There should at least be tickets...

2044
01:18:36,073 --> 01:18:37,466
What do we do if there aren't any?

2045
01:18:37,466 --> 01:18:39,232
I think I can only relax
once we're on the plane.

2046
01:18:39,232 --> 01:18:41,459
We're treating this plane ride
like it's just hopping on a bus.

2047
01:18:41,459 --> 01:18:42,878
[Will they be able to achieve
their dream of going to Jeju?]

2048
01:18:42,878 --> 01:18:44,250
- Tangerine farm experience.
- Picking tangerines.

2049
01:18:44,250 --> 01:18:46,546
- We can make money there...
- By picking tangerines?

2050
01:18:46,546 --> 01:18:47,697
- We pick tangerines...
- Yeah!

2051
01:18:47,697 --> 01:18:49,252
- and bring tangerines back with us.
- Yeah.

2052
01:18:49,252 --> 01:18:52,560
So during the livestream,
we'll hold tangerines. Like this.

2053
01:18:53,854 --> 01:18:55,666
"We brought these from Jeju."
